title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg, chilies, cheese and taco seasoning mix.
Mix well and pat into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake uncovered.
Remove and let stand 10 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix by directions on box. Add cinnamon, brown sugar and honey and mix well.
Bake cake in thin layers one at a time.
Once each layer is done, place on cake plate and add applesauce mixture to hot layers.

title: greek chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer on low heat for 3 hours.

title: curry dip for raw vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving with raw vegetables.

title: shortcake biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in shortening. Add milk.
Either roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness and cut into biscuits, or pat into a 9-inch square cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits test done.

title: cheeseburger rice
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet on medium-high heat; drain fat.
Stir in water, catsup, mustard, salt and pepper. Bring to boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover.
Let stand 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Garnish with lettuce leaves, pickle and tomato slices.

title: taco chili salad
directions: Prepare chili according to package directions; cool.
Reserve 2 1/2 cups chili.
Wrap remaining chili tightly; freeze for later use.
Fry tortillas in 2 inches hot oil, pressing down centers with large ladle to form shell.
Continue frying until crisp and golden; remove with tongs.
Drain.
Arrange greens in taco shells; top with chili, process cheese food, tomatoes, avocado and olives.
Serve with sour cream and additional process cheese food, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp tree
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add crab and shrimp boil.
Boil for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and bring to boil again.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Chill shrimp.
Peel and devein shrimp, leaving the tails on, if so desired.

title: sock-it-to-me cake 1
directions: Blend Duncan Hines butter mix, sour cream, sugar and oil and add eggs, one at a time.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Oil and flour cake pan.
Then pour 1/2 batter in pan, then add sugar mixture, then add rest of batter.
Bake at 320° for 55 minutes.

title: dip for fresh fruit
directions: Mix ingredients; ready to serve.
Just dip fruit into mixture and eat.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with sugar, baking soda, eggs and sour cream.
Take 3/4 of the dough and spread into a greased jelly roll pan.
Spread on top with pie filling.
Roll out remaining dough on floured board and cut into strips.
Make lattice work on top. Brush top dough with egg whites and sprinkle with nuts if desired. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cook any cake mix as directed.
Cool.
Mix flour and milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Whip together.
Ice cake.
It is surprising how much this tastes like a Twinkie.
Best with yellow cake.

title: easy tater casserole
directions: Place hamburger in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread soups over the hamburger.
Lay Tater Tots all over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: italian crispy broccoli with fettucine
directions: Heat oil in wok or skillet and add broccoli.
Cook, covered, for 4 minutes, stirring occasionally until tender crisp.
Add red pepper flakes, garlic and ham and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Transfer mixture to a bowl and add red pepper, fettucine and chicken stock to the wok.
Cook, covered, 3 or 4 minutes or until heated through.
Add broccoli mixture and salt and pepper to taste and combine well.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Serves 4.

title: shipwreck
directions: Brown hamburger with salt, celery and onion.
Place in layers in baking dish (at least 2-quart) the meat, beans and potatoes; repeat.
Add tomato soup on top and dot with butter.
Cover dish and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: peach jello pie
directions: Bring sugar, water and cornstarch to a boil, then add Jell-O. Take off stove and cool.
Peel and slice the peaches.
Put in the crust.
Pour the mixture over peaches and chill.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Serves 8 people.

title: pink surprise pie
directions: Cover apples with pineapple.
Drain just before serving. Combine apples and pineapple; spoon into
pie shell.
Fold yogurt into Cool Whip; mound onto filled pie.
Top with strawberries or red raspberries and garnish with daisies.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Stir in sauce.
Simmer.
Cook noodles.
Combine egg and cottage cheese (mix well).

title: tie-dyed french toast
directions: Whisk together eggs and milk.
Pour eggs evenly into 4 small bowls.
Add desired amount of food coloring.
Dip toast corners in each bowl.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Cook bread until brown on both sides.
Repeat until all is gone.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Line bottom of a large baking dish with bacon strips.
Pour dry rice over bacon.
In a bowl mix soups and water together; pour over rice.
Arrange chicken on top and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: ham and potato scallop
directions: Cut ham in serving pieces and place in greased dish.
Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick over ham.
Melt butter in pan, stir in flour, then tomato juice and milk.
Stir and cook until thick. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes and ham. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip breasts in eggs, salt, pepper and then in bread crumbs. Brown in oil.
In saucepan, combine tomato sauce, garlic powder and basil.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Add margarine to sauce and reserve crumbs from skillet (after browning breasts). Arrange breasts in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over breasts, then pour sauce over all.
Put Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix cranberry sauce with Russian dressing and soup mix.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick-n-easy chocolate fudge
directions: Grease pan or dish and set aside.
Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave until all is melted.
Pour into greased dish and let sit until cool and firm.
Cut into squares.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat together egg yolks and sugar until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in orange juice and melted butter.
Stir in salt, lemon rind, tarragon and sweet potatoes.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; fold into sweet potato mixture.
Turn into buttered 1 quart casserole and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until set and lightly brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: holiday pecan cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, brandy extract and egg yolks in food processor.
Add flour and salt to butter and sugar and mix in food processor.
Roll dough mixture into 1-inch balls.
Coat in 2 egg whites saved from before, then roll in chopped pecans.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Press each ball with a deep thumbprint in middle of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Check frequently.

title: spice bars
directions: Mix raisins and water; boil 10 minutes slowly with 1 stick oleo.
Let cool.
Then add sugar, soda, flour, generous teaspoon of cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Mix and bake in greased and floured pan 9 x 13-inch at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and cover.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix onions, tomatoes, peppers, Spam or ham and mayonnaise. Mix with cooked macaroni.
Let set overnight or a few hours before serving.
Drain macaroni before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour; cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Gradually add broth.
Bring to boil for 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Pour into greased 2-quart shallow baking dish. Place biscuit mix in medium bowl.
Cut in 3 tablespoons softened butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown meat with onions; drain well.
Add cheese, parsley, flour, onions and mushrooms.
Stir these gently together.
Spoon into pie shell.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over all in pie crust when you're ready to bake.
You may make this ahead and pour milk and eggs on when ready to bake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set for 5 minutes before cutting.
Travels very well for potluck.

title: sinful salad
directions: Mix together well and chill 3 to 6 hours.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Boil syrup and sugar.
Add peanut butter and melt.
Mix in corn flakes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.
No bake candy is ready.

title: *cheese bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in honey or sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure water into a large bowl and sprinkle in dry yeast.
Stir until dissolved, then add to warm milk mixture.
Add cheese and flour; mix well.
Dough should be non-sticky to fingers, smooth and satiny.
Place dough into greased bowl and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and divide into 2 portions.
Let rise on bread board for 10 minutes.

title: sausage pasta
directions: Place sun-dried tomatoes in one-cup of water.
Cook sausage meat, breaking into pieces, while cooking.
Remove from pan and drain grease.
Saut chopped onion and garlic in olive oil until translucent.
Add fresh chopped tomatoes and stir.
Cook five minutes.
Add sun-dried tomatoes and water, stirring mixture together.
Cook 10 more minutes.
Add fresh peppers, scallions and cooked sausage meat.
Stir together.
Add remaining ingredients (except pasta) to taste.
Cook several minutes longer.
Cook pasta. Place cooked pasta in a bowl and top with sauce.

title: family favorite barbecue beans
directions: Mix all together and bake, uncovered, in oven approximately 1 hour. Do no cook in crock-pot or overcook.
We like them juicy.

title: pecan roll
directions: Mix in a large pan and then roll in coconut.

title: choco bananas(guatemala)
directions: Peel bananas, put a frozen Popsicle stick into each banana, freeze overnight.
Cover bananas with chocolate coating.
(Use method for melting chocolate on candy bag.)
Serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: homemade pizza dough
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl allowing yeast to soften.
Stir in oil and 2 cups flour.
Add more flour until dough holds together.
Grease your hands lightly and knead dough on floured board until smooth.
Cover and let rise 45 minutes.
Shape it to pans you are using or into individual disks all on greased pans.
Brush with sauce and cover with ingredients.
Let rise about 5 to 10 more minutes then bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes. This recipe also makes a nice French bread loaf.
My family makes individualized pizzas.

title: fudge
directions: Melt cheese, butter and vanilla together.
Add powdered sugar and cocoa.
Mix together; pat onto ungreased cookie sheet (2). Use a paper towel to pat out to catch excess butter.
Let harden.

title: beulah's fruit cake
directions: Cream well together margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add soda, which has been dissolved in the water.
Add lemon extract and mix thoroughly.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix dates, raisins, pecans and candied fruits with about 1/4 of the flour.
Mix remainder of flour into the sugar, butter mixture, then add fruit and nut mix and stir until thoroughly blended. Beat egg whites and fold in.
Spray a large tube pan with nonstick spray.
Pour in batter, making sure it settles down into pan. Bake at 275° for 3 hours until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: devil dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended. Drop by spoonsful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in 350 oven for 10 - 15 minutes. Makes about 30.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle first 5 items in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting. Refrigerate any remaining pie.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: avocado magnificent
directions: Place cubed avocado and diced tomato in a bowl.
Squeeze lime juice over mixture.
Lightly salt with 2 dashes of garlic salt. Blend well.
Serve with garlic pita chips.
Serves 2.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Drain juice from vegetables.
Add vegetables to softened cream cheese and cut in mayonnaise. Season to taste.
Spread on bread slices.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: ragu turkey wings
directions: Coat wings with flour.
Saut 1/2 of chopped onion in deep fat until clear.
Add wings and fry until brown.
Place wings in baking pan; cover with 1/2 chopped onion, 1/2 chopped bell and 1 stalk celery, chopped.
Pour on Ragu sauce.
Bake at 350° until done (about 20 to 30 minutes).

title: creamy coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each. Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in vanilla and coconut. Beat egg whites, add cream of tartar and continue beating until stiff. Fold whites into batter. Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9 inch pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: canning green tomatoes
directions: Slice the green tomatoes,
as
you
would
if
you were frying them.
Place in wide mouth jar.
Put 1 teaspoon salt in on top of tomatoes.
Fill
jar
with	lukewarm
water, leaving 1-inch headspace.	Seal
and
place in lukewarm water bath and cold pack for
minutes.
(Let water boil for 10 minutes.) Set off heat; cool
and
store.
When ready to use, open jar, drain off water and prepare as you would fresh.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Cook the rosamarina as directed. Use large pot with lots of water.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and salt to pineapple juice.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Mix with rosamarina and cool in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate syrup(for chocolate milk or topping, etc.)
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Store in refrigerator.
Use in milkshakes or combine 2 tablespoons syrup with 1 cup milk and heat for hot cocoa.

title: won tons
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.
Let stand at least 1/2 hour so flavors blend.
Place 1/2 teaspoon filling near center of won ton skin.
Moisten edges and fold in triangles.
Pinch to seal.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Mix beef, hot dog pieces and all other ingredients in a large pot or bowl. Divide into 2 casserole dishes (2 to 3-quart size each).
Bake for about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: lemon delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix 1 1/2 cups flour with 1 stick margarine and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Press into baking glass (9 x 13-inch) dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until brown.

title: fresh pineapple sherbet
directions: **The juicy pieces of diced fresh pineapple give it a texture and flavor that makes it different...and better...
than any other sherbet you've ever tasted.
Good fresh, ripe pineapple could have a completely green shell color, or more often, a shell with green and gold.
The leafy crown should look fresh and green. The fruit should feel firm.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Put beef slices between sheets of plastic wrap.
With flat side of mallet, pound until about 1/4 inch thick.
Dip beef into the beaten egg and then into bread crumbs, mixed with salt and pepper.
Heat fat in heavy skillet over medium to low heat.
Brown steak 8 to 10 minutes on each side.
Place steaks on warm platter. Keep hot.

title: gooey marshmallow puffs
directions: Separate crescent rolls into 4 triangles.
Dip marshmallows in melted butter; roll in combined mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Place 1 dipped marshmallow on each crescent roll.
Wrap to enclose marshmallow; seal edges.
Dip in melted butter; place in muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Drizzle over rolls.
Serve warm.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Let set until sugar dissolves (while you are preparing your fruit and nuts).
Mix your eggs with sugar mixture; mix until well blended.
Mix in vanilla, fruit and nuts. Sift flour, salt and soda together; mix in with sugar and fruit mixture.
Blend well.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Using extra duty aluminum foil, form platter type container. Alternate layers of sliced potatoes, onions, butter pats, salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Wrap foil from end to end and close by crimping top together tightly.
Place on a barbecue grill for 30 minutes along with other foods.
Due to heat elements, cooking time may vary.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Add pudding mix to the milk.
Add Eagle Brand.
Stir in milk. Add Cool Whip; stir.
Layer vanilla crackers and bananas, beginning with the crackers.
Pour some mixture over each layer.
Refrigerate overnight (very important).

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to creamed mixture, mixing until blended. Tint with food coloring, if desired.
Cover and chill dough.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Pour over boiling water and bring to a boil.
Cook until thick.
Refrigerate until cool, but not set.
Fold in fresh strawberries.
Put in a baked pie shell. Top with whipped cream.

title: porcupines
directions: Soak rice for 1/2 hour in water.
Rinse thoroughly and combine with other ingredients except tomato soup or puree.
Mix thoroughly and shape into balls.
Place in a roaster pan and pour 1 can tomato soup or puree over top.
Add sufficient water to come to halfway up the meat balls in pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
After removing the balls, thicken the juice for gravy.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the first 5 ingredients one by one. Dilute the can of soup with 1 1/4 cups of water and the 3/4 cup of Miracle Whip; mix well. Pour half of the liquid mixture over the layers in the pan. Lay the chicken pieces over rice and liquid mixture. Add the remaining liquid mixture on top of the chicken. Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour. Makes a great meal.

title: hot drink
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, lemon slices and water. Boil 5 minutes. Strain. Add lemon juice, orange juice, pineapple juice and apple cider. Heat, but do not boil.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter. Add flour, stirring constantly, until smooth. Remove from heat and slowly add milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Stir in corn, egg and cheese.
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Combine water, barbecue sauce, bread crumbs egg, parsley, onion and celery.
Add meat.
Mix well.
Put into meat loaf pan. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: four way meatballs
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix lightly, but well.
Shape into 16 meatballs.
Place in an 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Combine boiling water and jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 4-cup mold or 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Brown the hamburger; drain. Combine with spaghetti sauce.
Use a 9 x 14-inch Pyrex dish. Layer spaghetti, cheese and meat sauce; repeat.
Bake at 350° in a regular oven for 30 minutes or bake in microwave for 14 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand a few minutes.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: pear pecan salad
directions: Drain pears.
Boil 1 1/2 cups juice, or use 1 cup juice and 1 cup ice cubes to set faster.
Mix with Jell-O.
Set to thicken in refrigerator.
Beat together pears and cheese.
(Don't drop the fibers from the pears back into the mixture; they will gather on your beaters.
Throw the fibers away.)
Add to thickened Jell-O. Mix in whipped cream and pecans.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours or longer.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler; beat with mixer 1 minute. Then place over boiling water and beat for 7 minutes, stopping a time or two to scrap sides. Do not over cook. Frosting should have more body than meringue but not stiff or thick-just creamy.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Pour beans in skillet.
Chop onion and add to beans and barbecue sauce; place bacon on top.
Cook in oven at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: little mexican pies
directions: Spray muffin pans with cooking spray.
In a skillet, brown the ground beef, then mix in the seasoning and sugar.
Separate biscuits into 2 halves and place one half in each muffin cup. Press bottoms and sides to form a cup; spread meat mixture into cups and sprinkle tops with cheese.
Bake according to biscuit pkg. directions until golden brown.
Makes 16 servings.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour, vinegar, reserved pineapple juice and egg in top of double boiler.
Cook until mixture is thickened.
Chill until mixture is cool.
Dice apples.
Add apples and pineapple to cooled mixture.
Fold in whipped topping.
Add the cocktail peanuts just before serving.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese and oleo together, then add the flour.
Chill for a few minutes.
Makes 2 dozen balls which you shape in tart pans.

title: pita pizza
directions: Wash and slice all raw vegetables.
Heat oven to 400°.
Half each pita bread and toast on both sides until golden brown.
Spread each half with 2 tablespoons sauce, 1/2 of vegetable mix, 1/6 cup Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 teaspoon Parmesan cheese and 1/2 tablespoon olives.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese starts to bubble and turn slightly brown.
Serve warm.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the Grape-Nuts and apple juice concentrate.
Pat into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 10 minutes, then cool before filling.

title: green jello
directions: Prepare jello, using half the water.
Add cream cheese and smash with fork.
Refrigerate until cool and slightly thick.
Add prepared Dream Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Mix and refrigerate!

title: ogre sandwich
directions: Open bun on cookie sheet.
Place pastrami, sauerkraut and Swiss cheese slices and heat thoroughly in oven.
Will feed 2 if sandwich cut in half.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan. Stir well. Place over medium flame, stirring constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°).
Stir in juice and rind. Remove from heat. Add pecans.
Stir until coated.
Spread on wax paper and separate into clusters with a
spoon.
Let cool.

title: lumpia
directions: Simmer last 3 ingredients in a frying pan, then add other ingredients.
Add salt and nutmeg to taste.
Cook until done. Scoop 1 tablespoon of the mixture into a lumpia skin and roll up. Glue with white of egg.
Deep fry until brown.

title: christmas breakfast casserole
directions: Prepare 24 hours ahead of time.

title: spicy sugared nuts
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix egg white and nuts, stirring until nuts are coated and sticky.
Mix the sugar, cinnamon and a dash of nutmeg.
Stir into nuts until evenly coated.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 30 minutes.
Makes about 2 cups!

title: chicken tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender in boiling water with 2 teaspoons salt.
Drain. Cook onion and green pepper until tender. Add flour and blend. Add milk and cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly. Stir in soup. Add tuna.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in microwave.

title: coconut pecan bars
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream butter well and add brown sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth and creamy.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Spread in buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into bars.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen bars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain.
Place in a buttered oblong casserole. Saute onion in margarine until soft. Remove from heat, blend in bouillon cube, mustard, salt and pepper.
Slowly add milk and soup; stir.
Then add mushrooms with the juice.
Mix in meat, vegetables with sauce mixture, spoon over spaghetti.
Sprinkle the cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If too thick, add a little more milk.
This can be frozen for future use.

title: steak and rice
directions: In large saucepan cook steak in butter.
Add soup mix and water to steak.
Cover and simmer until sauce is a little thick (approximately 30 minutes).
Pour over rice.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: depression dinner
directions: Mix together (like a meat loaf) and shape into patties (14). Wrap a slice of bacon around edge of each and secure with toothpick.
Grill.

title: cookie pizza pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pizza pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 cup oats and 6 tablespoons margarine at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, blend in egg.
Press in prepared pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in sweet potatoes and water.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Fold in pecans and raisins.
Spoon into 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until it tests done.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar, and eggs. Mix well. Add remaining ingredients in order listed, one at a time. Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: harvest potatoes with herbs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a small bowl, combine seasonings. Place 2 tablespoons melted butter in a 10-inch skillet (if handle is not ovenproof, wrap with foil).
Arrange a third of potato slices in circular pattern in skillet.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon of seasonings, 4 teaspoons melted butter and 2 tablespoons onion. Repeat layers twice, cover tightly with foil and press layers down.
Bake 20 minutes.
Uncover; bake 20 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven; press layers down with a spatula.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving platter to unmold potatoes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add mayonnaise, soup and onion.
Add to broccoli. Cut cheese into small pieces and mix throughout.
Top with crackers.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Sprinkle coconut into bottom of pastry shell.
Pour mixture over coconut.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Season chicken with peppers and salt.
Coat with flour.
Brown in oil in large heavy pot.
Remove chicken.
Cook the 4 vegetables until soft.
Put chicken back in pot and cover.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Add rice and mix together 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour beer and water over and mix.
Add 2 teaspoons salt and cook slowly until rice is done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat loaf with red gravy
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients until well blended. Then shape into an elongated loaf.
Place meat loaf into a 9x13 pan or small roaster.
Next pour tomato soup all around the meat loaf, along with 1 can of water.
Slightly mix water and soup with a fork.
Cover
and bake in a 350 degree oven for 1 1/2 hours or until juices run clear when forked.
Baste with gravy one or twice during baking time.
Uncover the last 15-20 minutes to brown.

title: fried pies
directions: Mix into 1/2 cup Crisco shortening with fork or pastry cutter. Add 2/3 cup evaporated milk and 1 beaten egg.
Pour to desired consistency.
Blend to mixture.
Roll out walnut sized balls of dough to make small circles of thin crust.
Add filling in middle of each crust, then fold in half and crimp along the edges with fork to seal.
Fry the pies in deep hot cooking oil until brown.

title: ziti a la nancy
directions: Cook ziti and drain.
Brown meat; stir in sauce and parsley. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella, egg, salt and pepper; mix well.
In a large deep casserole or crock-pot, put a layer of sauce first, then alternate layers of ziti, cheese and sauce, ending with sauce. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes or in a crock-pot at medium setting for about 4 hours.

title: spiced cider
directions: Bring all ingredients to the boiling point.
Strain and serve hot in mugs.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, butter, cocoa and milk; simmer. Add peanut butter, vanilla, salt and oatmeal. Quickly put on wax paper.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour; cook and stir until bubbly.
Gradually add chicken soup; cook and stir until thickened, about 5 minutes. Stir in the milk, cream, basil, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Add the vegetables; cook gently until heated through.
Yields 8 to 10 servings (about 3 quarts.)

title: pecan-topped coffee cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: carrot soup
directions: In a 3 to 4-quart pan, combine oil and onion.
Stir over medium heat until onion is limp.
Add curry powder and flour; stir about 30 seconds.
Add broth and carrots.
Cover and simmer until carrots are tender when pierced, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add parsley.
In a blender or food processor, whirl about half of mixture at a time. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Soup can be served hot or cold.

title: marna's cheese cake
directions: Put cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream in a large bowl; let stand until room temperature.
Mix sugar, flour and cornstarch in a small bowl.
To the eggs, add vanilla and lemon juice; have handy.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Measure all ingredients into glass bowl.
Stir thoroughly. Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Especially good on shrimp, but may be used on other seafood.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: golden ham pie
directions: Saute onion and pepper in the 1/4 cup salad oil.
Remove from heat and blend in flour until smooth.
Stir in 2 cups milk and chicken soup.
Bring to boil and add diced ham and lemon juice. Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with cheese biscuits made by mixing Bisquick and cheese with enough milk to roll out and cut into biscuits.
Bake at 400°
for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix and serve on ice.

title: ham rolls(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: With fork, mix cream cheese with milk.
Add Worcestershire sauce, onion, pepper, basil and thyme.
Stir.
Spread cheese mixture on top of each slice of ham.
Roll up the ham.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Slice in 1-inch circles before serving.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and liquid ingredients separately.
Pour liquid into dry ingredients and mix.
Spoon into muffin pan, about 3/4 full.
Bake about 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Test with toothpick at 25 minutes.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite size pieces.
Melt butter on medium heat.
Saute mushrooms, garlic and onion until tender. Remove from pan.

title: blackberry yogurt muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Paper line, or spray with Pam, muffin tin. In a large bowl, combine oat bran, brown sugar and baking powder.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Make cake according to directions and bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Meanwhile, drain pineapple; set aside.
Take one small package pudding, make according to directions.
Then add 8 ounce package cream cheese and mix well.
When cake is cooled, spread mixture on top of cake, then spread on pineapple.
Spread Dream Whip on top.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: The thyme, marjoram and bay leaf are optional.

title: spicy zucchini corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Coat 10-inch cast-iron skillet with oil. Heat over medium heat.
Whisk milk, eggs, and chipotle in large bowl.
Stir in corn muffin mix, zucchini, and cheese until just combined.
Spread in hot skillet.
Bake 21-23 minutes until set in center and top is evenly browned.
Cool in skillet on wire rack at least 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6-8.

title: quick apple betty
directions: Spread apple pie filling in a baking dish.
Mix margarine, brown sugar and graham cracker crumbs together.
In separate bowl spread crumb mixture over top of apple pie filling.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Brown crumbs.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla, mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and blend in.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Shape batter in 1 inch balls.
Place in ungreased tiny muffin tins, bake 8-10 minutes.
Remove immediately and press a peanut butter cup in each until only top shows.
Let cool before removing from tins.

title: limeade dressing(club member: leslie jordan)
directions: Blend all ingredients with rotary beater.

title: mini appetizer pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large skillet, brown ground beef and sausage. Mix onion into sausage and beef mixture and saute it until tender. When meat is browned and onion tender, drain the grease out of the skillet. Stir processed cheese into meat and onion mixture. Continue cooking until the cheese melts. Arrange slices of bread on a cookie sheet. Place a heaping spoonful of the meat, cheese and onion mixture onto each slice of bread. Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Serve warm. Makes approximately 20 servings.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients very well.
Add milk and cook until thick. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Refrigerate.
Heat amount needed in microwave for ice cream or desserts.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix
1 stick melted butter, 2 eggs and yellow cake mix. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter, then add mashed bananas.
Add eggs, buttermilk (mixed with soda), sifted dry ingredients and nuts. Bake at 350° in a well-greased loaf pan for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter as for pie crust; set aside.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add with the milk to the flour mixture; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, divide dough into four equal parts.
On a lightly floured board, roll each portion into a 12-inch circle. Brush with 1 tablespoon of melted butter and cut into 12 pie-shaped wedges.
Roll up, beginning with the wide end, and place on greased cookie sheets.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Let rise in warm place until nearly doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Freeze in a plastic bag.
Defrost as needed.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with water; beat well.
Add pudding mix and beat.
Put in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
In a large 3-quart bowl, spoon about 1/4 of the pudding mixture.
Top with 1/4 of the fresh strawberries and 1/4 box of the vanilla wafers.
Alternate layers, ending with pudding mixture.
Garnish with 6 crushed vanilla wafers and a few strawberry slices.

title: punch
directions: Fill a Bundt pan 1/2 full of Hawaiian Punch and a Bundt pan 1/2 full of pineapple juice and freeze.
These will be used to float in the punch to keep it cold.

title: stir-fried collard greens
directions: Remove stems of collards and discard them.
Wash leaves thoroughly.
Slice leaves into bite-size pieces by rolling several leaves together and cutting into 1/4-inch strips.
Blanch greens in boiling water for 30 minutes.
Drain well.
Heat drippings in wok or large skillet until hot.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir-fry until vegetables are tender, about 4 to 5 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Soften yeast in water.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
With a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut butter into flour mixture.
Add yeast mixture and milk.
Stir until well combined.
Cover; set aside for 30 minutes.
Roll or pat dough out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds with 3-inch cutter.
Place biscuits on lightly oiled baking sheet.
Prick tops with fork.
Set aside for 45 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake biscuits until golden and firm on top, 15 to 18 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 12 delicious biscuits.
Perfect with any meal.
Good recipe for beginner cooks.
Happy eating.

title: maduros
directions: When selecting very ripe plantains, the skin should be very black and they are slightly soft.
Peel plantains and slice 1/4-inch thick diagonally.
Heat 1-inch oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Fry until golden brown (2 to 3 minutes per side); drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.

title: chex and chocolate party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal, coconut and peanuts in large shallow pan.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and corn syrup to boiling.
Without stirring, boil 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over cereal mixture; stir until pieces are evenly coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool completely, stirring frequently to break mix apart.
Add chocolate chips and raisins.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 16 cups.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Put sugar and water in saucepan.
Dissolve cornstarch in as little water as possible and stir into sugar and water mixture; cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and coloring.
Place strawberries in bottom of baked pie shell.
Pour filling over strawberries and chill.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter and cocoa into pan.
Bring to boil; cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter, nuts and vanilla.
Stir well and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let stand 1/2 hour to cool and dry.

title: cheese dip
directions: Put in crock-pot and heat.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up and boil chicken.
Lift chicken from broth; cool and debone, placing chicken back into broth.
At this point, you may need to add more water.
Bring to boil and add salt and pepper and bouillon cubes.
While water is coming to boil, prepare dumplings.

title: asparagus, petits peas and mushroom casserole
directions: If using fresh asparagus, wash clean, cut spears into approximately 2 1/2-inch lengths.
Cover with water and cook, just until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Arrange around the outer edges of a buttered casserole dish, stacking on each other.
Drain peas and fill in the center of casserole.
Mix grated onion, mushrooms, cream of mushroom soup, grated cheese and pepper.
Pour over asparagus and peas.
Toss crumbs or potato chips over top. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until crumbs are brown. May be made ahead of time and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: belen's enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken in a large pot.
Wash peppers and remove seeds. In a small pot boil pepper in a little water until peppers are soft.
Put peppers, cumin, garlic and water in a blender and blend until smooth.
Heat stove to medium high.
Heat oil in frying pan. Put chili sauce in a large bowl.
Drain and separate boiled chicken.
Dip tortilla in chili sauce.
Fry tortilla in frying pan for 2 seconds on each side.
Put chicken in fried tortilla and roll up like a burrito.
Repeat for all tortillas.	Chop lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve hot enchiladas with rice, lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and hot sauce.

title: treasure bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine cereal and milk.
Let stand 2 minutes. In small bowl, combine oil and 1 egg; stir into cereal mixture. In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add to cereal mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in raisins.
Spoon into greased and floured 2 1/2-inch muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with wire whisk to remove lumps. Add oil and next 3 ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Pour batter in Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Enjoy!

title: milk gravy
directions: When sausage, ham or bacon has cooked, remove from skillet and keep warm. Pour fat that has accumulated in the skillet into a heat-proof measuring cup. Return 1/3 cup to the skillet. Add flour and cook over medium heat about 5 minutes, until flour no longer smells raw. Add milk all at once and cook, stirring constantly, until gravy is thick, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Add salt.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Remove from pan and dry on paper towel. Remove some of bacon grease.
Add vinegar to frying pan.
Cook to simmer.
Put bacon back in pan.
Pour over lettuce and stir.
Eat while warm.

title: squash bake
directions: Layer vegetables, starting with squash, then zucchini, tomatoes and onion. Sprinkle with basil. Repeat in a 1 3/4-quart casserole dish sprayed with vegetable cooking spray. Melt margarine and sprinkle over ingredients. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Makes 6 servings.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, adding sausage and eggs last.
Pour into 2 (1 1/2-quart) casserole dishes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wieprzowina with smietanie (baked pork chops in sour cream)
directions: Salt and pepper the pork chops on both sides and fry in margarine until brown; then place in casserole.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour mixture over the chops.
Bake, covered, for 1/2 hour in preheated 350° oven.
Makes 4 servings.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Fold in pineapple and Cool Whip.
Pour mixture in pie crusts.
Put in icebox.

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Put in one bowl and mix 3 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peppercorn chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken between sheets of plastic wrap.
Pound with a mallet to about 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle with peppercorns.
Heat a heavy skillet; add butter and chicken.
Cook, turning once, until chicken is done, about 5 minutes.
Remove chicken and keep warm.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook rice.
Add thawed broccoli.
Add soup, cheese and milk. Saute celery in oleo and add.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crab cakes
directions: Put shrimp in food processor; add egg, salt and pepper. Process until blended.
Slowly add heavy cream while processing. Remove from processor and add mixture to crab and carefully blend. Add mustard, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and onion.
Shape into patties and put on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until ready to cook (at least a half hour).
Fry until golden brown in oil.

title: fried corn patties
directions: In blender or food processor, combine corn and water.
Do not puree.
Add eggs and process briefly.
Put this mixture in bowl. Add all remaining ingredients, except oil (it is for frying), mixing well.
Heat oil, about 1/2 to 1-inch deep in skillet.
Drop 1 to 2 tablespoons of mixture into heated oil.
Fry to 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: chocolate fudge parfait(serves 1)
directions: Layer strawberries and pudding in parfait glass.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: castillian sauteed broccoli with olives
directions: Cut broccoli into 2-inch lengths.
Saute garlic in oil and butter in skillet for 1 minute. Add broccoli and stir-fry 5 to 7 minutes. Add olives.
Stir gently.
Cover and let steam for 3 to 4 minutes. Add salt.

title: nutmeg feather cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and vanilla. Bake in 2 greased and floured square layer cake pans in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: potato filling
directions: Peel potatoes and grate.
Drain in colander.
Squeeze excess water out of potatoes.
Saute celery, onions and parsley in butter. Add grated potatoes and egg and season to taste.
Stir and cook over low heat until potatoes are thoroughly cooked.
Filling need not be completely done if baked in a casserole in oven.
Filling can be put into any type of fowl.

title: meatza pie casserole
directions: Combine beef, garlic salt, bread crumbs and milk in bowl, using fork to mix.
Spread evenly in the bottom of 9-inch pie pan, raising a rim about 1/2-inch around edges.
Spread catsup over meat; arrange the drained mushrooms over catsup and cover with cheese.
Sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meats and place in large stock pot with all other ingred.
Simmer 4-5 hours.

title: meat spaghetti sauce(a recipe to enjoy from the kitchen of sarah surina.)
directions: Chop garlic and onion very fine.
Saute in little oil until golden brown.
Add tomato paste and water and simmer 2 minutes. Then add tomatoes, oregano, bay leaves, sugar, salt and pepper. In a separate pan braise pork bones and pork for 15 minutes.
Then add them to tomato sauce.
Let everything cook uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at a simmer.
Brown the ground chuck in oil.
Drain off fat and add meat to the sauce.
Cook the sauce an additional 45 minutes, skimming off the grease.
Cook pasta.

title: beans supreme *
directions: Wash and pick over beans.
Put beans and next four ingredients in an electric bean pot.
Mix well.
Cover with lid and cook overnight, 9 to 10 hours.
Drain beans, leaving as much liquid as desired.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 1 to 2 hours. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: beef soup
directions: Steam ground beef, garlic and onion together. Drain and put in a large soup pot. Add juice, sugar, bay leaf and cream of celery soup. Microwave carrots and celery until tender. Add to soup mixture. Simmer for 1/2 hour. Add salt and pepper. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Skin chicken breasts and cook in salted water until tender. Debone and cut in bite size pieces.
Mix all together.
Put in pastry lined dish.
Cover with top crust.
Make vents in crust and bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then roll out on floured board and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry frozen dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Watch carefully, stirring for 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread in 10 x 13-inch pan and save some to sprinkle on top.
Beat the next four ingredients.
Beat 1 cup whipped cream and fold into mixture. Pour over crumbs and sprinkle remainder on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: apple salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together apples, pineapple, small marshmallows and chopped pecans.
Cook until thick the sugar, juice from pineapple, salt, cornstarch, egg, butter and vinegar. Let cool and pour over apple mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: silly putty
directions: Pour starch in a bowl.
Add glue and let set for 5 minutes. Add food coloring.
Mix until starch is absorbed and color is spread smoothly.
The more you mix, the better it gets.
Store in an airtight container overnight.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: In a large skillet, quickly brown pork chops in 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil.
Drain excess fat.
Combine pineapple chunks and juice with barbecue sauce, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Turn and baste chops. Stir in green pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes longer or until chops are tender.
Add more barbecue sauce, depending on your taste.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.

title: ruth baker chip dip
directions: Add last four ingredients to taste.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.

title: heavenly orange fluff
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and orange concentrate.
Chill until partially set.

title: spinach soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender; remove from skillet with slotted spoon.
Stir in flour, then milk.
Puree spinach with consomme; add mixture to sauce.
Add seasonings.
Stir in cream; mix well.
Heat just until simmering; stir in sherry.
Sprinkle with almonds before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix with beans and taco seasoning.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream and taco sauce.
Place meat mixture in greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread sour cream mixture over beef mixture.
Place cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sparkling cranberry punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine cranberry cocktail and lemonade concentrate.
Stir in sparkling water.
Serve immediately.
Makes 25 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: bunny sundae
directions: Mix 3 or 4 drops of food coloring with the coconut.
Use this for "grass" in 4 small bowls.
Cut 4 red or pink jelly beans in half.
In each bowl, put 2 scoops of ice cream.
Use jelly beans for ears, small red candies for eyes and nose, and a miniature marshmallow for a tail.
For a fluffier bunny, cover ice cream with whip cream first.
Sprinkle a few jelly beans on the coconut and enjoy!

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve with fruit.

title: english silk pie
directions: Beat 1/3 cup butter or margarine with 6 tablespoons confectioners sugar until smooth.
Add 3 eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: strawberry pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in pineapple syrup.
Add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir in lemon juice.
Chill until thick.
Halve berries and 1 cup pineapple chunks to mixture, then chill until firm.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in water.
Add lemon juice and salt. Cool and blend in sieved cottage cheese.
Whip cream and fold in with walnuts.
Put on top of layer.
Fill center with berries and rest of pineapple chunks.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool.
Add 2 tablespoons of vanilla and stir well.
Add 1 quart of vodka and have fun!

title: chocolate covered raisins
directions: Spoon chocolate over raisins until well coated.
Spoon onto mounds on wax paper.

title: ham loaves
directions: Pour over loaves and bake 1 hour.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar, Karo syrup and salt in a microwave safe dish and cook for 4 minutes on high.
Stir and cook 3 1/2 minutes more on high.
Stir and add butter and vanilla.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes more.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet and spread to desired thickness with a spatula.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: italian rabbit fettuccine
directions: Rinse rabbit pieces in 2 tablespoons vinegar.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add the sliced onion, rabbit and ham.
Saute gently, about 5 minutes, on each side.

title: shamrock silk pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions for filled one crust pie.
Refrigerate remaining crust for later use.
Heat oven to 375°.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and flour, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add chocolate, eggs and 1/4 cup Irish mist liqueur; mix well.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Pour into pie crust lined pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean; cool.
Combine remaining whipped topping, 1 tablespoon Irish mist liqueur and food coloring.
Spread over pie.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add sugar and eggs, then other ingredients. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: luscious lemon shrimp
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish; add shrimp (in shells), lemons, cooking wine, herb spice, salt and Accent.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Saute sausage in skillet until brown; drain off fat. In a mixing bowl, add cooked sausage to Bisquick and cheese, stir until well blended.
Add a little water to make mixture gooey.
Make small balls and bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add milk, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Stir in rice and raisins.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: foolproof chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt morsels with Eagle Brand.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly onto wax paper-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 to 3 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature. Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: sandra's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Combine sugar, 3/4 cup warm water, salt and oil.
Add yeast.
Stir well.
Add flour.
Mix to smooth, soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Place dough in greased bowl; cover and let rise until at least doubled (about 2 hours).
Make into rolls; brush with melted butter; let rise until very light.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit slush
directions: Boil together 3 cups water and sugar.
After coming to boil, remove from heat and add cold water.
Blenderize together the bananas, pineapple and cherries.
Mix all together with thawed orange juice concentrate.
Freeze in individual plastic cups or 9 x 13-inch pan to scoop out.
Let sit out several hours before serving for eating consistency.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Melt and set aside butter.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend in egg and milk.
Add butter.
Mix altogether no more than 25 strokes quickly, just until moist.
Add blueberries. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.

title: hot cranberry butter
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and water in a saucepan. Heat to boiling, stirring until sugar dissolves. Boil until the berries pop, about 5 minutes.
Add brown sugar and butter.
Heat until dissolved.
Serve hot on French toast, waffles or pancakes.

title: ice cream snow
directions: Mix it all together with a wooden spoon and then share it with your friends immediately.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender, drain and cool slightly.
Mince pepper.
Cut onion in round slices, separate and mix with carrots. Mix other ingredients together and pour over vegetables. Marinate 12 hours or more.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Note:
You may use any vegetable you like.

title: baked ziti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease shallow baking dish.
Mix ziti, hamburger, 1 1/2 cups marinara, 1/2 cup Mozzarella and the Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses in casserole.
Top with remaining sauce and Mozzarella.
Cover and bake 45 minutes until hot.
Serves 6.

title: wild rice with mushrooms and almonds
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add rice, almonds, onions and mushrooms. Cook and stir until almonds are brown, about 20 minutes. Pour rice into a baking dish. Heat broth to a boil. Stir broth into rice mixture. Cover tightly and bake for about 2 hours in a 325° oven until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender and fluffy.

title: microwave pecan treats
directions: Place milk and chips in microwave and melt.
Take out and cool.
Dump in marshmallows and pecans; stir.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in jam.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Mix with soups, sour cream and almonds.

title: chocolate fruit pie
directions: Mix all together in bowl and put in one (9-inch) pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients well so oil does not separate.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Cool at room temperature.
Mix lettuce, tomatoes, onion, cheese, beans and oregano.
Toss well.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Mix as listed and pour in a casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Method of combining is very important. Combine all ingredients except oil, dissolving over low heat. Cool and add oil just when ready to combine salad. Shake to mix.

title: apple crunch
directions: Arrange in greased baking dish in order listed.
Bake at 350°, covered with foil, for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer or until done.
Serves 20.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender except cheese, ham, shrimp, bacon and mushrooms.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Sprinkle with unblended ingredients and push them down below the surface of the egg mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: southern sweet potato muffins
directions: Combine the 1/4 cup flour and brown sugar.
Using pastry blender or knife, "cut in" margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Set aside for topping.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook and peel potatoes.
Dice them.
Fry bacon and onions and remove from pan.
Crumble bacon over potatoes.
Drain off all but 1/2 cup of bacon fat.
To this, add vinegar, sugar, flour, salt, mustard, celery seed and water.
Cook until thick, then mix with potatoes.
This can be made a day ahead and reheated in a slow oven (300°).
Makes 15 servings.

title: quick doughnut drops
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and beat until thick and creamy.
Add salt, butter, dry ingredients and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Drop by teaspoons into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: roasted potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into wedges lengthwise.
Put butter and oil in baking dish in 325° oven to melt butter.
Toss wedges in mixture to coat.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika mixture. Bake 1 hour, turning potatoes occasionally.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix well until light yellow. Sift together flour and cinnamon. Stir into egg mixture.
This will be very stiff.
Add vanilla, apples and walnuts, stirring until well mixed.
Pour into greased 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: blond brownies
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure 1 cup.
Add baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
Sift again.
Set aside.
Melt margarine; then add sugar and mix well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts.
Turn into greased 9 inch square pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan, then cut into squares.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with chopped onion and bell pepper in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Put seasoning in tomatoes and pour into the meat mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn muffins
directions: Blend dry ingredients together.
Beat egg and milk; add to mixture until moistened.
Put into paper lined muffin tins, 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugars, milk and butter; cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until marshmallows melt.
Remove from heat.
Stir 30 seconds longer. Pour into 8-inch buttered pan.
Let cool.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Put 8 slices of buttered bread, butter side down, in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Add ham and cheese. Add other bread slices. Set aside. Combine the eggs, salt, pepper, dry mustard and milk. Pour over bread, cheese and ham.
Refrigerate overnight (cover with Saran Wrap).
Next morning, mix corn flake crumbs and oleo. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy in double boiler.
Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add candy; beat well.
Mix flour, salt and soda; add to this mixture with milk.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: southwestern rice and bean salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar with flour in top of double boiler; add 1 whole egg and 3 egg yolks and add milk and blend thoroughly.
Cook uncovered over boiling water until thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Layer in baking dish custard, wafers and bananas, ending with custard.
Stand wafers around edge of dish.
Whip remaining 3 egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until stiff peaks form. Spread over custard, touching wafers all around.
Bake at 425° until delicately browned.

title: dorothy's pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and vegetable oil.
In another bowl mix flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Combine with first mixture; mix, then add pumpkin.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes for sheet cake, 35 minutes for layers (makes 2 layers).
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk on stove top; do not boil.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish with butter and set aside.
Set milk off stove and add bread, sugar and butter.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add salt and vanilla.
Gently stir bread mixture into egg mixture and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set dish in a pan of water on bottom shelf of oven.
Put approximately 1 inch of water in pan. Bake for 1 hour.
Insert wet knife into the pudding.
If knife comes out clean, it is done.

title: ham and egg rolls
directions: Peel eggs and cut in half.
Roll each half of egg in slice of ham.
Secure with toothpick.
Arrange lettuce leaves around on plate.
Arrange ham and egg rolls on lettuce.
Decorate with pickles and mayonnaise.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: little links in pillows
directions: Lightly grease two 12-cup muffin tins.
Separate 2 cans of dough into individual biscuits.
Place in pans.
Sprinkle lightly with sesame seed.
Top with 1-inch square of cheese.
Press one sausage deeply into center of each biscuit.
Bake 10 minutes in 425° oven.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Makes 4 dozen biscuits.
Can be frozen.

title: holiday fruit ball
directions: Cream
together
cream	cheese and confectioners sugar. Add fruit and
nuts.
Mix
well. Shape into a ball.
Roll in 1 cup chopped nuts.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Beat eggs and vanilla in a large mixing bowl at high speed until thick and lemon colored.
At low speed, add dry ingredients, mix thoroughly. Heat milk and butter in saucepan just to boiling.
Gradually add to flour mixture.
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
When completely cool, ice with 7 Minute Icing.
Sprinkle top and sides with coconut.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Beat sugar into egg whites until folded in.
Fold in pecans, crackers and vanilla.
Butter a 9-inch glass pie plate well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: brenda's tater tot hot dish
directions: Lightly grease baking dish and crumble hamburger on bottom. Add vegetables and mix hamburger.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Mix soups together and spread over Tater Tots.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
It should be brown and crisp.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: barbecups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 cups in a muffin pan.
Mix chopped onion with ground beef and brown in a skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Add brown sugar.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits. Place 1 biscuit in each greased muffin cup; press firmly in bottom and up sides, forming rim around the top.
Spoon about 1/4 cup meat mixture into each biscuit-lined cup.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges of biscuits are golden brown.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cooked banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour pudding mix, and salt in a 3 quart heavy pan. Stir in egg yolks and milk. Blend well. Cook, stirring constantly until thickened. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Spread small amount on bottom of 3 quart casserole. Cover with vanilla wafers. Top with layer of 2 sliced bananas. Pour about 1/2 of custard over bananas and layer all again, with the rest of the custard on top. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Gradually, add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until stiff peaks form. Spoon on top of pudding spreading over entire surface all the way to the edge. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and blackberries.
Bake in 3-layer cake pans.
This is especially nice topped with chocolate icing.

title: gumbo
directions: Boil chicken, sausage and onions until chicken and sausage are well done.
Add seafood, okra, bay leaves, thyme, salt, black pepper, crushed red pepper and gumbo file.
Serve over rice. Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer 1/2 hour.
This is good for poultry, beef, pork and venison.
Will keep for up to 6 months in glass jar in refrigerator.

title: easy bake chicken
directions: In glass dish or pan, place 4 to 6 pieces boneless chicken. Mix together mushroom soup and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Place 4 to 6 pieces of Swiss cheese over top of chicken.
Top with croutons.
Pour butter over croutons.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered; 15 additional minutes uncovered.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Combine all ingredients except the chocolate chips; mix until blended.
The mixture will be crumbly.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread chocolate chips over hot cake.
Let chips soften, then spread evenly over bars.
Cut into bars.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk, then flour, sifted with cinnamon.
Pat into an ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Pour unbeaten egg white over surface; drain off excess.
Sprinkle nuts over top, pressing down lightly.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars while hot.
These freeze well.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: microwave turkey directions
directions: Wash turkey.
Rub with salt, especially inside cavity.
Place, breast side down, on large microwavable dish.
Halfway through, turn breast side up and cover leg and wing ends with aluminum foil to prevent overcooking.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients with salt and pepper and spread in greased casserole dish.

title: banana homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Heat well.
Stir in bananas.
Pour mixture into container of 1 gallon.
Save room at the top for ice cream expansion.

title: spring potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Reserving water in pan, remove potatoes to colander and rinse under cold water to cool.
Drain and cut into 1/2 inch dice.
Add carrots to reserved water and cook about 3 minutes until tender.
Remove from water, rinse and drain.
Add fresh peas to reserved water and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
If using frozen, thaw and drain well; do not cook.
Toss potatoes with sherry or broth, vinegar, tarragon, salt and pepper. Add carrots, peas and mayonnaise.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: ground beef and potato casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with 1/2 of beef, half potatoes and a layer of onions.
Repeat.
Pour soup over it all.
Cover and place in oven at 350°.
Bake 2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: key lime pie
directions: In large heat-resistant bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in yogurt with wire whisk. Fold in whipped topping with wooden spoon. Spread in crust. Refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: tanya's party time cheese ball
directions: You may add 1 (2.25 ounce) jar of Armour dried beef, finely chopped.

title: greek rotini salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain; cool.
Combine lemon juice, olive oil, spices and garlic in container.
Mix until well blended and of a thick and creamy consistency.
Chill.
Combine cooled pasta with rest of ingredients and large bowl.
Pour dressing over salad and toss gently to coat evenly.
Serve immediately.

title: taco pie
directions: Add taco sauce to beef. Sprinkle 1/2 cup corn chips over pie shell.
Put meat mixture over chops, then spread sour cream.
Add cheese on top of sour cream and top with remaining chips.

title: meatloaf
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, salt and pepper to taste. Place in loaf pan.
Mix tomato sauce, vinegar, and mustard for topping and pour over meatloaf.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Layer and cook 5 hours.
Add cheese last hour of cooking.

title: cinnamon apple rings
directions: Cut cored and pared apples into 1/2-inch rings.
Cook all ingredients until apples are just tender.
Chill.
Instead of the cinnamon candies and red coloring, use 12 whole cloves and green coloring.
Makes a nice showing at Christmas.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the sugar, cocoa and milk for 1 minute.
Add oatmeal, coconut and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Combine 2 1/4 cups flour, yeast, sugar, butter and salt.
Stir in warm water, mix until soft dough forms.
Add remaining flour if necessary.
Turn onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth, about 4 minutes.
On lightly greased baking sheet, roll dough to 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread dressing down 1/3 center of dough.
Top with layers of beef, cheese and sauerkraut.
Make cuts from filling to edges of dough 1-inch apart on both sides of filling.
Alternate sides, folding strips at an angle across filling.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes in warm place.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with caraway seed.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: no bake cherry pie
directions: Bring cornstarch, sugar and water to a boil over low heat. Boil about 2 minutes until thick and clear.
Stir in gelatin dessert until dissolved.
Add cherries.
Chill until mixture starts to set, then fold in whipped topping.
Pour into pie shells. Chill.
Yield:
two 8-inch pies.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add garlic, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in large amount of boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients except Mozzarella.
Layer half the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with half the Ricotta filling.
Add half the cheese, then half the meat sauce.
Repeat layers, reversing the last two.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes, or until cheese on top is golden.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour 1/2 into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels and margarine and can of milk in microwave and pour over baked cake, add chips, if desired.
Add remaining cake batter and finish baking 30 more minutes.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal; mix well.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.
Let stand to cool before handling.

title: manhattan meat roll
directions: Sift flour, baking powder
and 1/2 teaspoon salt into a mixing bowl.
Cut in
shortening
with
pastry
blender
until mixture resembles a fine meal.
Add
milk
all at once and mix to form a soft dough.
Use a lightly floured board.
Put dough on the floured board and
knead lightly about 20 times.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake
in
oven
for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Place sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and quickly add peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let stand to dry.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.	Put 1 package of dry onion soup in bottom
of	casserole
dish.
Add
dry
rice
and
layer of chicken pieces.
Mix
1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 can of water;
pour over chicken.	Cover and bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours.	Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels (not too fine) and mix with sugar and butter. Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cook 6 minutes at 400°.
Cool. Cream 1 cup sugar and cheese, then add Cool Whip.
Mix well and pour over crust.
Chill approximately 2 hours.
Add 1 large strawberry Jell-O mixed with 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Spread on top of salad; chill.

title: cherry breakfast rolls
directions: Add margarine, water and milk that have been heated until just warm.
Stir in sugar, salt and dry yeast.
Slowly add flour to make a soft dough, saving 1/2 cup flour to add during kneading.
Knead on floured board.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning once. Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Divide into 20 pieces.
Roll each piece into 15-inch strands.
Wind into a coil.
Allow to rise for 2 hours on baking sheet.
Indent center and add about 4 cherries. Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Combine powdered sugar, vanilla and milk.
Drizzle over cake.

title: chicken-asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, water chestnuts, almonds and chicken in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Combine next 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon mixture over chicken, sprinkle cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch dish and spread undrained pineapple over bottom.
Add the blueberries.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar.
Crumble cake mix on top of fruit layer.
Drizzle melted butter over top of dry cake mix.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
After cake has cooked 25 minutes, cut down through it in several places so juice can come to surface.

title: beef or chicken stew
directions: Put all ingredients, except wine and frozen peas, together (season with salt and pepper) and stir well.
Put in oven at 250°. Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup water after the first hour.
After the third hour, add either white or red cooking wine.
Continue baking at 250° for 5 hours.
Stir every hour.
The last hour, put the box of frozen peas on top.
Cook covered.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan. Stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla. Gradually pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Turn into two shallow 12 x 15-inch pans. Bake in preheated oven at 250° for 20 minutes. Empty into large containers.
Work fast.
Break apart.
When cool, store in airtight container (Ziploc bags).

title: anne's hearty spaghetti sauce
directions: In large pot, brown sausage and ground beef together.
Cover pot and drain fat.
Add onions, stirring until lightly brown. Drain rest of fat.
Add all other ingredients and simmer approximately 4 hours, stirring frequently.
Serve over thin spaghetti or vermicelli.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Rinse raisins and nuts in boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased muffin pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter may be refrigerated and used as needed.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: life's recipe
directions: (A recipe passed on through the ages.)

title: scalloped hash browns
directions: Mix. Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole and cover with Italian bread crumbs.
Drip stick of oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: In microwave-proof bowl, add margarine, onion, celery, garlic and 1/2 cup bell pepper; saute.
Stir.
Cook slowly with top on, stirring often.
Add 1 1/2 cups water, 2 cups
chicken broth and 1 can shrimp bisque.
Cook 20 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with cold water.
Add shrimp.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: crock pot french dip
directions: Mix together water, soy sauce and all spices.
Pour over roast and cook in crock pot on high for 6 to 7 hours or until tender.
Remove and shred meat.
Butter and broil rolls.
Make sandwiches with meat and use juice in crock pot as dipping sauce.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add shortening, eggs and banana to dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions and celery.
Cook until vegetables are transparent.
Mix in remaining ingredients and pour into greased casserole, saving 1/4 cup noodles for topping.
Top with crushed noodles saved for topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crazy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles or macaroni; drain. Brown meat; pour off fat. Add season salt and all ingredients except cottage cheese and cheese in a 2-quart pan. Layer macaroni, cottage cheese, meat sauce and 1/2 cup cheese. Repeat layers, ending with cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves at least 8 big eaters. Serve with salad or garlic bread.

title: banana-chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine oil, honey and eggs.
Beat in bananas; set aside.
In small bowl, mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Add oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Add to banana mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Line muffin cups with paper baking cups or spray with nonstick spray.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: anytime fruit cobbler(blueberry, apple, peach, etc.)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour small amount of the margarine in bottom of 8 x 12 baking dish (2-quart baking dish or 9 x 13 dish); set aside.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and rest of butter together well.
