Pour into baking dish.
Place fruit evenly over top of this. Do not stir!!
Bake at 375° until lightly browned, about 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Store leftovers in fridge covered.

title: one step lasagne(microwave recipe)
directions: Using cook/drain container, cook ground beef for 4 to 5 minutes at 100% power.
Salt; add water and sauce to beef.
Mix egg, Parmesan and Ricotta cheeses and parsley.
In 9 x 13-inch dish or 2 smaller dishes spread 1/3 sauce.
Cover with 1/3 dry noodles, 1/3 cheese mixture and sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella.
Repeat twice and top with remaining meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover tightly with double thickness of plastic wrap.
Cook for 30 minutes at 50% power.
Uncover; sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and additional Parmesan.
Cook, uncovered, at 50% power for 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Allow to stand for a few minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Remember if using 2 small dishes, cook only 1 at a time, but for 1/2 the time.

title: super chicken supper
directions: Have chicken delivered from favorite local take-out service. Immediately destroy cartons and bags and other "tell-tale" evidence of delivery.
Place chicken on baking sheet.
Liberally sprinkle spices over pieces.
Reheat chicken in 250° to 300° oven. No one will ever know.
Serve with tossed salad and bowls of pasta topped with butter and Parmesan cheese.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Use electric skillet at 400°.
Add sugar, syrup and butter; stir until sugar is dissolved (about 5 minutes), then add peanuts. Cook, stirring constantly, about 5 to 7 minutes.
"Do not brown." Then add soda.
Cut off heat; stir fast and pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes and cut out stems.
Slice about 1/2 inch in thickness.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Coat with corn meal and cook in heated cooking oil in skillet.
Brown both sides. Serves 6.

title: pork and veal casserole
directions: Brown the meat.
Add soup and water.
Cook 1 1/2 hours slowly. Add rest of the ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
I often use all pork.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Brown onions and peppers with hamburg.
Add tomatoes, syrup, salt, pepper, chili powder and bay leaf.
Simmer 15 minutes. Blend cornstarch in meat mixture; add macaroni or rice.
Put in 2-quart dish.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Add 1 cup cheese over last 15 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put pecans in bottom of Bundt pan.
Mix cinnamon and sugar. Roll the biscuits in sugar mixture.
When well coated, place in pan.
Mix melted butter with remaining sugar mixture and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix the spaghetti with all the other vegetables and pour dressing over mixture and serve cold.

title: "great" meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, 1/3 cup of soup, bread crumbs, onion, egg and salt. Form into loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Blend remaining soup, 2 or 3 teaspoons of drippings and water.
Pour over loaf.
Bake another 10 minutes.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter with sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts, beating well after each addition.
Add nuts, then the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions. Mix all together and cook 2 1/2 hours.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all but carrots, onions and green pepper.
Once marinade is mixed, add carrots, onion and green pepper.
Chill overnight, tossing occasionally.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter, 1/4 cup of powdered sugar and vanilla with a spoon.
Blend in flour.
Gradually mix in nuts.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls, rolling in palms.
Place about 1/2-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 325° for 30 minutes until light brown.
Then move to wire rack.
Still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll again.
Store in container.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix
and sift together flour and soda.	Add alternately with first
ingredients, then add pecans and vanilla.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Set out cream cheese, eggs, butter or oleo and flour overnight so they will be at room temperature.
Cream butter and cream cheese together; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift together flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture clings together.
Press in to 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Beat together eggs, white sugar, lemon juice, flour and baking powder.
Pour over baked crust and bake 20 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: thunder cake
directions: To take this thunder cake, you do it this way.
You start counting when you hear thunder and then, when you see lightning, you stop counting.
If your number is 10, that means it is 10 miles away, and if it is that close, you need to hurry up and make a cake.
It is just a normal cake, but you make it in a storm.
It is done in a storm, so it is a thunder cake, and it is sort of a good recipe.

title: delicious pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with wire whisk.
Gently stir in the Cool Whip.
Layer bottom of pie crust with mixture.
Mix 1 cup half and half and the pudding mix; let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the pumpkin, cinnamon, ginger and cloves; mix with wire whisk. Put over other layer in pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.

title: brussels sprouts and carrots
directions: Cut large Brussels sprouts in half.
Heat 1/2 cup water, lightly salted, to boiling.
Add sprouts and carrots.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cook, covered, 10 to 15 minutes or until tender-crisp; drain.
Return to saucepan.

title: tender soda pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Beat eggs, milk and melted butter just until blended and add to flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Using a 1/4 or 1/2 measuring cup, drop batter on hot, lightly greased griddle.
Bake.
Brush with melted butter and serve immediately.
Makes 11 to 12 (5 1/2-inch) pancakes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook and drain 8 ounces lasagna noodles. Brown ground beef, onion and garlic salt together.
Drain.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano. Simmer uncovered for 20 minutes.
Layer noodles, meat and cheese.
Make sure cheese is last layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish coffee cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients like pie crust.
Divide and roll into 2 long strips on cookie sheet.
Pat to 1/4-inch thick.
Bring to boil 1/4 pound oleo and 1 cup water; add 1 cup flour.
Remove from stove.
While hot, add eggs, 1 at a time.
Stir well after each addition.
Add almond flavoring.
Spread over pastry to 1/4-inch from edge.
Bake in a 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook hash browns according to directions on package.
Mix hash browns and next 6 ingredients.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch buttered casserole.
Top with crushed corn flakes; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together well.
Dip with fresh strawberries.

title: justin's slaw
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil and then cool.
Pour cooled mixture over the cabbage, onion and pepper.
Refrigerate.
Can be kept several days.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces (bite-size).
Cut grapes in half.
Add mayonnaise for desired consistency.
Grapes should be one-third amount of chicken.
Add curry powder to taste (sprinkle first).
Decorate with slivered almonds.
Serve on lettuce or use for appetizer on cocktail breads.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables and stir in vinegar mixture.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: raisin rice pudding
directions: Bring water to boil in large saucepan.
Add rice.
Cover and cook until tender.
Drain rice, rinse with cold water and set aside.
Place 1 quart of milk, sugar, salt and raisins in double boiler and heat slowly.
Blend cornstarch with remaining half cup of milk.
Beat eggs until light.
Add vanilla to eggs, then stir into cornstarch mixture.
Slowly add cornstarch mixture to milk mixture in double boiler, cooking and stirring until mixture coats on spoon.
Remove from heat and fold in rice.
Chill.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, sausage, eggs, onion, ketchup, salt and pepper together.
Add oats a little at a time.
May add more than 3 cups. Divide in 1/2 to make 2 loaves.
Put ketchup on top of loaves. Bake in a 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Spray loaf pans with Pam oil spray.
Combine eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; set aside.
Combine other ingredients.
Add to zucchini mixture; stir.
Pour in pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat fat; add onions.
Stir.
Lower heat until onions are brown.
Add remaining onions and celery.
Add pepper and butter. Cook 5 minutes.
Add hot sauce, thyme, basil and 1/2 cup stock. Cover.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes; stir. Lower heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce; simmer 5 minutes.
Add remaining stock and sugar; stir.
Simmer 15 minutes. Add shrimp.
Turn off heat.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Place all ingredients in the food processor and blend until very small chunks of vegetables remain.
You may have to scrape the sides of the bowl a few times to get all of it chopped.

title: venison roast
directions: Combine all ingredients into crock-pot until done.

title: coconut pie(self crust)
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Alternately add milk and dry ingredients to shortening mixture.
Add vanilla and bananas.
Bake for 1 hour in loaf pan at 350°.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Make macaroni and cheese ad directed on the box.
Put in a casserole bowl and add tuna, peas and cream of mushroom soup. Sprinkle crackers over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese and bacon dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except vegetables.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix in a bowl the sugar, milk and flour.
Pour peaches over. Melt butter in dish, then pour into dish over the butter.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Arrange in 3-quart Pyrex baking dish. After cooking and deboning chicken, break chicken into large chunks and place on top of broccoli.
Mix undiluted soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Top with bread crumbs, tossed in butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: polly's cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, eggs, oil and mandarin oranges with the juice and bake as instructed on cake mix box.
Bake at 350°.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Add peanut butter and 2/3 cup milk.
Mix until damp.
Beat 2 minutes at low speed.
Add 1/3 cup milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with Chocolate Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: m'jaddara
directions: Wash lentils under running water.
Put them in a cooking pan with just one cup of water and bring them to boil over high heat, 5-7 minutes.
Lower heat and cook, covered for 15-20 minutes or until water is absorbed.

title: lauren's care-a-lot candy
directions: Put peanut butter in a big bowl and mash with a spoon.
Add the maple syrup and stir.
Put in the sugar a little at a time and keep stirring.
When you cannot stir any more, use your hands.
Squeeze and pound the candy until smooth.
Now pour in the granola.
Mix it into the candy with your hands.
Break off little of candy.
Make each one into a small ball about the size of a marble.
Put the candy in the refrigerator.
Leave it there for at least an hour. Now your candy is cold and crunchy.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Mix the ingredients and pour into the dish.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and mix with 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken broccoli tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix soup and milk together. Mix chicken, broccoli, 1 cup of the cheese and 1/3 to 1/2 of the milk mixture. (Use enough soup mixture in the above ingredients to keep it moistened good.) Spoon mixture into each tortilla. Roll up and place in greased oblong casserole dish (size of dish depends on if using small or large tortillas). Pour rest of milk/soup mixture over all the roll-ups. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly. Top with onion rings and return to oven to be browned. (Can be prepared ahead and frozen, baking at a later date. Allow a little more time for baking when coming right from the freezer. Add onion rings after it is hot and bubbly....brown.)

title: thanksgiving brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt butter, then add brown sugar.
Add eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Mix and put mixture into oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and let partially cool.
Cut into squares.

title: paul's pumpkin bars
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and cooking oil.
In another bowl sift together all dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture alternately with pumpkin to beaten mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
See cream cheese frosting recipe.

title: ham and cheese pinwheels
directions: Unroll and separate crescent rolls into 8 rectangular shapes. Press the diagonal cut in each sheet to seal the dough.
Spread each sheet with 1/4 teaspoon mustard (more or less to taste).
Lay a piece of ham on top; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Roll in sesame seed.
(If time allows, place on a plate and refrigerate for a few minutes, makes them easier to cut.) Slice in 1-inch pieces.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix last three ingredients.
Pour over first four ingredients. Chill.

title: "tricky torte"
directions: Slice pound cake into 7 layers while cake is cool from the refrigerator.
Melt chocolate bits and stir in sour cream.
Evenly frost all layers, including top layer.
Top with sauteed almonds, pressing lightly so they will not fall off when cake is sliced. Refrigerate.

title: sylvia's cheese ball
directions: Mix at room temperature.
Chill.
Roll into ball, then in chopped nuts.
Can be frozen.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil the chicken breasts in large pot filled with water, 1/4 teaspoon salt, celery, carrots and onion. Remove the chicken from the pot, saving the liquid, celery, carrots and onion. Remove the chicken from the bone and break into bite size pieces. Return the chicken meat to the pot. Add 1 can chicken broth and pepper. Bring to a rolling boil. Mix the Bisquick and milk in a large bowl. Roll out onto floured surface to about 1/2 inch thickness. Using your hands, form 1 inch balls from Bisquick dough. Drop into boiling broth. Cook, uncovered, at gentle boil for 20 minutes. Check dumplings for doneness.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Mix all but pecans together.
Add to pecans.
Spread on baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 20 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Cool.

title: breakfast bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line 1 package rolls on bottom.
Beat cream cheese; add yolk, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put other crescent rolls on top and press edges together.
Beat egg white and brush on top of rolls.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle evenly in greased pan, 9 x 13-inch.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and chopped nuts together in a large bowl.
Stir in melted butter and mix with your hands until light and crumbly.
Remove 1 cup of the mixture to be used later as topping.
Place remainder in an 8-inch square pan and press firmly.
Bake at 350° or about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add molasses and egg.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll in small balls; dip into sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pinch cake
directions: Place nuts in buttered Bundt pan.
Take each biscuit and cut into 4 pieces.
Roll each 1/4 biscuit in cinnamon and sugar mixture; cover well.
Place sugared dough in pan, placing layer of raisins after each can.
When finished with all cans, melt 1 1/2 sticks butter and pour over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes, then flip onto cake plate.

title: party punch
directions: Mix jello as directed on box.
Pour juices together and mix with jello mixture.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer about 1 1/2 hours before serving time.
Allow to become slushy.
Add ginger ale or Sprite.

title: roasted  pepper pasta
directions: Cook noodles as directed. Slice peppers in 1/2 and hollow out inside. Place hollow side down on a cookie sheet. Wipe olive oil on the outside of peppers and sprinkle with kosher salt. Broil until peppers turn black (approximately 15 minutes). Wipe skin off with a paper towel and thinly slice. In a pan, add diced onion, diced tomatoes, garlic and fennel seed. Add peppers and toss with cooked pasta and fresh basil. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: tuna ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain tuna.
Mix all ingredients, except parsley, and form into a ball.
Sprinkle with parsley and then place in refrigerator to cool.
Serve with crackers.
Ball can also be rolled in nuts.
Makes 12 servings.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in dish.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and vanilla flavor. Mix all together and pour in on top of melted oleo.
Put 1 cup of blueberries on top (last).
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix applesauce and baking soda together.
Mix cut up walnuts and raisins together with flour and set aside.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients together with the applesauce mixture and raisin mixture.
Pour into a tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well all of the ingredients and store in an airtight container.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; beat well.
Set aside. Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form; fold into peanut mixture.
Spoon into crust.
Sprinkle with peanuts and chill.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Mix butter, nuts, salt, vanilla and powdered sugar. Add flour. If too stiff, add a little more milk. Roll into fingers and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple pecan pie
directions: Blend Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice; drain crushed pineapple.
Mix to other ingredients.
Put in graham cracker shell and chill for at least one hour.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix and roll in 4 rolls; put in refrigerator.
Slice and bake on ungreased baking sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: good walnut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into roll.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Slice and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot dip
directions: Chop up all ingredients and mix together.
Pour Italian dressing over all and mix well.
Let set for a couple of hours and serve with tortilla chips.

title: pat's husband pleasing meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce, water, oats, egg, onion, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Add ground meats, mixing lightly but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Drizzle ketchup over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Drain grease from pan.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: lentil spaghetti sauce
directions: Serve on spaghetti and cover with lots of cheese.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix together and pour in a 9-inch crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: After preparing, bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick jello salad
directions: Mix all together in bowl; stir.
Leave Jell-O in powder form. Very good.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs. Mix soda, salt and flour.
Mix in oats and raisins.
Drop dough by spoonfuls on baking pan. Leave room for cookies to spread.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: "mary love's" potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes and mash.
Mix all other ingredients with the mashed potatoes, except almond slivers.
Spoon into casserole dish (flat and shallow is best).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Add butter pats to top of casserole and sprinkle slivered almonds on top.
Broil until bubbling.
Serves about 8 people.

title: cracked wheat salad *
directions: In large saucepan, combine water and bulgur.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes or until water is absorbed and wheat is tender, but not mushy.
Transfer to a bowl and refrigerate, uncovered, until cool.
Add pecans, currants, parsley, olive oil, orange zest, can of mandarin oranges (or orange, cut up), salt and pepper to taste and orange juice to taste.
Serves approximately 12 side dishes.

title: pimiento and cheese
directions: Shred cheese.
Add pimiento, chopped bell pepper, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add mayonnaise and stir.
Use enough mayonnaise to mix and be able to spread on bread.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in water.
Remove and cut up chicken in smaller pieces.
Return chicken to water and add butter, soup, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cut up one package of flour tortillas in long strips.
Drop into boiling mixture.
Boil for 5 minutes. Thicken with mixture of 5 tablespoons flour and cup of water. Easy, quick dinner.
Serve with hot cornbread.

title: butter crunch candy
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan; add sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook, stirring occasionally until it reaches 300° (hard crack).
Quickly stir in nuts and spread out on cookie sheet. Cool, then spread with melted chocolate.
Break into pieces after it cools.

title: baked chicken parmesan with linguine
directions: Grease baking dish.
Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Put into a shallow dish.
Dip chicken in eggs, then in bread crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken in casserole dish.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella. Bake until cheese is melted.
Prepare linguine as directed on package; drain.
Toss linguine with sauce.
Top with chicken.

title: kringla
directions: Mix sugar and oleo.
Add egg, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill dough until firm.
Roll a teaspoon of dough on a floured board and make a figure "8".
Bake at 350° until brown on bottom.

title: chicken and wine a la sandra
directions: In a frying pan, melt butter.
Add potatoes, onion, 1/4 teaspoon red pepper and garlic powder.
Saute until tender, then add bread crumbs.
In a shallow dish, put oil and garlic cloves. Pound cutlets and add a couple of tablespoons of stuffing.
Roll and place, flap down, in baking dish.
Add cooking sherry, water and 1/4 teaspoon of red pepper.
Cover with foil for 40 minutes. Remove foil and bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cook time:
1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix thoroughly and bake in an iron skillet at 450° until brown, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Blend first four ingredients and 1 teaspoon salt.
Stir 10 cups of water in apples.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add lemon juice and coloring.
Put in pint jars and boil in bath water 15 minutes; quart jars for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: eggplant with cumin rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat butter in ovenproof casserole, add eggplant.
Sprinkle occasionally with salt and pepper while cooking until soft, not mushy.

title: pizza with sun-dried tomatoes and goat cheese
directions: Add garlic powder or crushed cloves to olive oil.
Heat lightly and let sit.
Hand shred chicken breast.
Slice mushrooms and onions.
Chop sun-dried tomatoes into small pieces.
Use about 2 tablespoons of olive oil mixture to lightly saute mushrooms and chicken.
Brush oil/garlic mixture onto pizza bread crust.
Don't overdo it; brush lightly.
Remove excess oil with a paper towel if it pools on bread crust.

title: saucy ham and potato bake
directions: Saute onion in butter, blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk, cook, stirring constantly until thickened. Add 1 1/2 c. cheese; stir until melted. Toss potatoes in cheese sauce. Reserving 1 cup of potatoes. Pour into 2 qt. casserole dish. Arrange ham and reserved potatoes on top of casserole, top with remaining cheese. Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chip or veggie dip
directions: Cook eggs, sugar, vinegar and salt in a double boiler or thick pan until thick; whisk constantly.
Cook and mix with softened cream cheese until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients to your taste.
Flavor improves if set overnight. Keep in fridge.

title: green bean cheese cake casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add sour cream.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add green beans and pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: heavenly banana pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine pudding mix and milk.
Beat for 2 minutes or until well blended.
Add the sour cream and 2/3 container of Cool Whip.
Beat for another minute.
To assemble the pudding, place a layer of vanilla wafers on the bottom of the container you plan to use.
Can use a trifle bowl.
Add a layer of sliced bananas, next a layer of pudding.
Repeat with a layer of vanilla wafers, a layer of bananas, and a layer of pudding.
The top layer should be pudding.
If you like a lot of vanilla wafers, add another layer of them on the layer of pudding.
Top with the remaining Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cook oatmeal in water and set aside. Mix all other ingredients together. Pour in cooked oatmeal. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13 pan until done.

title: sweet 'tater puffs
directions: Add beaten egg, salt and pepper to potatoes.
Form in a ball around the marshmallows.
Roll in flakes.
Drop in piping hot Crisco until brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour and cocoa real good, then add eggs and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
When thick, remove from stove and add butter and vanilla.
Pour in a baked pie crust.

title: paradise salad
directions: Drain canned fruits.
Mix with cottage cheese and whipped topping in bowl.
Add jello.
Mix and refrigerate 1 hour.
Can be easily doubled.

title: seasoned potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover for 15 minutes or until tender. Drain and mash. Add green onion dip, cream cheese, butter, milk and garlic salt, beating at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth. Spoon potato mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel, wash and slice potatoes in baking dish.
Beat eggs and milk together with salt and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown around edges.

title: western supper
directions: Prepare dinner as directed.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti. Put remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Add spaghetti. Toss. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Slice up cucumbers; put into containers.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil; let cool.
Pour mixture over cucumbers. Will keep for 1 year.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In large saucepan cook onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Combine onion mixture in bowl with chicken and peppers; set aside.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all but 1/2 cup cheese together; spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese on top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon velvet european ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and lemon juice.
Add whipping cream and lemon extract.
Add grated lemon rind.
Add enough milk to fill up to fill line of ice cream freezer.

title: diabetic apple or pear pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir together fruit, cinnamon, tapioca, shortening and concentrate; allow mixture to sit for 10 minutes.
Pour mixture into pie shell; put on top crust.
Bake 1 hour or until top crust is golden.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In large bowl, mix ingredients together.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 box of crushed cheese bits cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fettucine florentine
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender, except noodles.
Blend. Cook fettucine according to package directions.
Put on warm plate and toss with sauce.

title: viola's corn pudding
directions: Bring cream and milk to the boiling point.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Let cool.
Beat each egg separately.
Combine with sugar and salt.
Add cream mixture.
Stir in corn.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: never fail rib roast
directions: Let meat stand out until room temperature.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place roast fat side up in a shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Do not cover.
Roast meat 1 hour; turn off oven and do not open oven door.
Thirty minutes before serving, turn oven on 375° again.
Carve in thin slices.

title: zucchini bread #1
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: the best pot pie
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and vegetables; reserve.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream cooked pumpkin, sugar and lard.
Add sifted ingredients and blend. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until light brown. Frost (if you desire) with 10x sugar and maple flavoring.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts.
Mix well and chill.
Shape into ball; roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat and add all ingredients, except rice.
Bring to a full boil.
Add rice; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for approximately 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add vanilla and almond.
Add flour and milk alternately. Pour in ungreased pan.
(Do not preheat oven.)
Start in cold oven. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Test.
I use a tube pan.

title: mother's tea cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, salt and eggs until light and soft. Mix and sift flour and baking powder. Add to the first mixture alternately with milk and vanilla, beating well. Grease cup cake tins or line with paper baking cups. Fill cups 3/4 full. Bake at 375 for 15 or 20 minutes. Yields 12 cup cakes.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Add all ingredients except crust and blueberries in a large mixing bowl, using a spoon to make sure it's all mixed in (no electric spoons).
Mix everything until it's smooth.
Then pour it in the graham cracker pie crust.
Put the blueberries on top, then chill in the refrigerator for at least 7 hours or overnight.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers together.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas, nuts and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix and chill.
Makes enough for an army.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Mix together cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple in a large bowl.
Add Cool Whip, condensed milk, nuts and marshmallows all together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; chill.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown onions and beef.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Put in casserole dish, leaving space for cornbread topping.

title: apple salad dressing
directions: Mix together the first 2 ingredients until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until thick.
Allow to cool.
Combine apples, celery and nuts and pour some of the dressing on top. Stir and serve.
Store balance of dressing in tightly covered container and keep refrigerated.

title: ten vegetable beef soup
directions: Boil
beef
until
done
and remove from broth.
If you want to	remove	grease,
you
need
to let broth get cold and grease will
be
on
top for easy removal.
Put broth in large kettle (10 quart)
to
make soup.
Add cabbage , green beans, potatoes, celery,
carrots,
onions
and lima beans.	Add V-8 juice and cook
hour
or
until vegetables begin to seem done.
Add corn,
peas
and tomatoes last.
Add water or beef bouillon as needed for flavor.	Cook another 1/2 hour and let stand for flavor.
Add beef back in soup, if desired.

title: cheesy turkey stuffing mix
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour stuffing mix into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Add cheese, turkey and pepper.
In a separate bowl, gradually stir milk into flour.
Stir in eggs.
Pour over stuffing mixture.
Bake 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: cheese dreams
directions: Have margarine and cheese at room temperature.
Cream well with mixer.
Add flour, salt and red pepper (cayenne) to taste; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies last (by hand).
Roll in wax paper (size of 50 cent piece).
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Cut in slices.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
May drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.

title: sausage gravy for breakfast
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Simmer until thick.
Serve over baking powder biscuits.

title: 5 pound fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Add 1 cup of flour to mixture.
Add 3/4 cup of flour to fruits and nuts. Mix the cream mixture with the flour, fruits and nuts.
Add flavorings last.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: easy roast beef and gravy
directions: Place roast in large piece of heavy aluminum foil.
Empty soup mix over meat; add soup.
Close foil so that steam does not escape but leaves an air pocket above meat.
Cook at 300° to 350° about 45 minutes per pound.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Cut cheese into small 1 inch pieces.
In a large bowl, combine all other ingredients and mash together thoroughly with a potato masher.
Store in refrigerator.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken in bottom of Pyrex casserole dish.
Combine soup and sour cream and smooth over chicken.
Combine crackers, poppy seed and butter; sprinkle over top of the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: solar pickles(canning)
directions: Put grape leaves at bottom of 1 gallon glass jar (about 2). Put salt, dill and garlic at bottom of jar also, layering pickles, grape leaves, garlic and dill until you reach the neck of jar, leaving 1/2 inch neck space.
Pour cold water and vinegar over the top of pickles.
Let pickle jar sit outside in sun for 48 hours. Store in refrigerator; good for 1 year.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Cream together sugar and butter; add 2 beaten egg yolks, raisins and pecans; set aside.
Beat egg whites very stiff, fold lightly into first mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: where's the beef ? cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into large ball; wrap and refrigerate.
About 1/2 hour before serving, unwrap and sprinkle with paprika.
You want the ball to be room temperature to serve.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Mix all but Cool Whip.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool well.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
After macaroni and cheese is done, add mushroom soup, then drain peas and tuna and add them to macaroni.
Stir together and serve.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in boiling water. Add flour and salt all at once. Stir vigorously. Cook, stirring constantly until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate. Remove from heat and cool slightly. Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously after each egg until smooth. Drop dough by heaping tablespoon 3 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in very hot (450°) oven 15 minutes, then in low oven (325°) for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in stock pot over low to medium heat.
Start with tomato products, mixing well, then add spices to taste; mix well.
Then add other ingredients.
Let sauce simmer a few minutes, then taste.

title: beef and spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; set aside.
Cook elbow spaghetti in 4 or 5 cups water for 7 to 9 minutes; drain and set aside.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw and drain spinach, pat dry with paper towel.
Mix in bowl with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Form into bite size balls and freeze or refrigerate until ready to use. Bake at 350° on cookie sheet for 20 minutes.

title: parmesan bread deluxe
directions: Preheat broiler.
In a small bowl combine cheese, dressing and onion.
Spread a generous teaspoon of the dressing mixture onto one side of each bread slice.
Arrange bread, dressing side up, on cookie sheets.
Broil 2 inches from heat for 2 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to mix directions.
Split cooled cake layers in half.
Combine sugar, sour cream and 2 cups coconut. Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for frosting.
Spread sour cream mixture between layers and on top of cake.
Combine reserved cup of sour cream mixture with Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth. Spread on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle remaining coconut on cake.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator for 3 days before serving.

title: jello pops
directions: Dissolve in hot water, then add cold water.
Pour into Tupperware popsicle molds.
Freeze hard.
Makes 12.

title: chicken taco pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cut into bite size pieces or fry ground beef.
Combine chicken or ground beef, taco sauce, soup, onion, garlic salt and pepper.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook together the broccoli, onion and butter, adding water as package directs.
Drain; cool.
Add soup, milk, rice and cheese. Put in baking dish; sprinkle with buttered crumbs or cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in bowl until
potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking or roasting pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry shortcake biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add 1/4 cup butter and shortening, thoroughly working them into the flour mixture. Lightly mix in the sour cream with a fork.
Add just enough milk to make a soft dough.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cook 2 minutes; boil, then add 1/2 cup miniature marshmallows and 1/2 cup semi-sweet chips. This will go with the Jackie Cake.

title: hot-cold slaw
directions: Bring the sugar, vinegar, oil, mustard, salt, and celery seed to a boil. Allow mixture to cool and pour over cabbage and onion. Refrigerate. Slaw will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: hawaiian toasts
directions: Spread toast with butter.
Place a slice of ham, pineapple ring and a cheese slice.
Cut each slice of toast in four with sharp knife.
Place on a greased baking sheet; sprinkle with the curry powder and allspice and cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: wonderful w. w. cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together until lumps are removed and it forms a creamy consistency.
Makes 8 servings, 1/2 P. and 20 c.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk and eggs; beat until mixed well.
Pour into a warmed greased iron skillet.
Bake at 425 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

title: polish bow ties(kruiciki)
directions: Combine yolks, sour cream, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add flour and make a stiff dough.
Place on floured board and knead until smooth, but not sticky.
Divide dough in two or three parts. Cover the parts with bowl.
Roll one part of dough very thin.
Cut into strips.
Cut each piece in center and pull through center. Fry in deep fat.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: nutty-crisp
directions: Place sugar, butter and nuts in heavy skillet.
Stir over low heat until nuts are toasted and sugar is caramel colored.
Pour onto foil.
Add salt.
Let cool.
Break into pieces and eat.

title: pinch me bread
directions: In plastic bag mix sugar and cinnamon.
Open 1 can of biscuits and cut each biscuit into fourth.
Place in bag with dry mixture. Shake until all pieces are coated, remove and place in Bundt pan. Spread 3 tablespoons of hot mixture over bread.
Repeat with second and third cans of biscuits.
Spread remaining hot mixture over last biscuits and sprinkle with remaining dry mixture.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let stand to cool for 5 minutes.
To serve just pinch off pieces.

title: romanian-style cheese pastry
directions: Mix together and sprinkle this mixture on top.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Have butter soft.
Add sugar and cream until light and fluffy. Add flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk small amount at a time.
Add flavoring.
Beat egg whites and fold in. Do not beat.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini and tomato au gratin
directions: Use 1/2 teaspoon oil to prepare 2-quart casserole. Cut tomatoes in bite size pieces.
Heat remaining oil in skillet.
Add onion rings and cook until limp.
Add zucchini slices, cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, juice, salt and pepper.
Mix carefully.
Turn into oiled dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: party dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Goes well with chips and vegetables.

title: cannelloni
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion. Add 1/2 jar spaghetti sauce, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup American cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted. Cook noodles according to directions on package. Stuff noodles with meat mixture.
Lay noodles in pan and cover with remaining spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix as given.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: grilled shrimp a la waco
directions: Cut bacon strips in half and wrapped peeled raw shrimp. Secure bacon with toothpicks.
Place on grill for 15 to 20 minutes.
Wrap jalapeno peppers with the shrimp to add some "spice."

title: beef stew
directions: Pull back husks to check condition of corn, but leave silk in place.
Leave 2 layers of husks on corn.
Rotate 1/4 turn halfway through cooking on High power; 1 ear 2 to 3 minutes, 2 ears 4 to 5 minutes, 4 ears 6 to 7 minutes, 6 ears 8 to 9 minutes, 8 ears 10 to 12 minutes.
If husks are removed, paper towel is also a good steam holder.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: Combine sugar, orange juice and rum and mix well.
Pour over berries and refrigerate 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix powdered sugar, peanut butter and cereal together.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls in chocolate.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and seasonings.
Add sauce and cook 20 minutes.
Layer Doritos, meat and cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese is melted.

title: pineapple tea
directions: Combine tea and sugar.
Add boiling water to dissolve.
Add pineapple juice, water and lemon juice; chill tea.
Pour 1/4-inch water into each section of 2 ice cube trays; freeze until firm. Place a cherry in the center of each cube in 1 tray; repeat with pineaple chunks in other tray.
Pour 1/4-inch water over fruit. Freeze until firm.
Fill sections with additional water and freeze until firm (freezing in stages prevents fruit from floating to top of cube).
Serve tea over fruited cubes; garnish with mint sprigs, if desired.
Yields 17 cups.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Place cocoa and baking soda in separate cups and mix each with a little hot water.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix well. Add buttermilk, cocoa and baking soda mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix in flour until smooth. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spicy salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: oh no, they're-staying-for-lunch casserole
directions: Combine chicken, 1/2 of stuffing, soup, broccoli and sour cream in greased casserole.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover with rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: In a large saucepan, mix sugar, salt and cornstarch; stir in vinegar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add butter, onions and beets.
Heat for 20 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together and fry in oil.

title: hamburger yum yum casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add soups.
Blend rice, celery and water.
Mix together and put in greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add noodles last twenty minutes (either on top or stir in).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes slightly.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine and mix with potatoes.
Mix other 1/4 cup margarine with corn flakes.
Mix remaining ingredients with potatoes.
Top with corn flake mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dietetic sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; cool slightly.
Mash until smooth; stir in rest of ingredients, including syrup from pineapple tidbits.
Return to stove and reheat.

title: fried dry pea patties
directions: Mash cooked peas; add eggs, salt, pepper, onions and flour. Pour oil in skillet and heat to medium-high heat.
Drop mixture by tablespoon into hot oil.
Brown on both sides.
Each serving contains 99 calories (47% fat).

title: grandmother hillhouse's funny tasting salad
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together. Stir until jello dissolves completely. Chill until syrupy.
Add next 3 ingredients. Chill until almost set. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Chill. Makes 6 to 8 cups.

title: springtime potato salad
directions: In a bowl, combine potatoes, celery, eggs, pickles, onion and radishes.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, milk, mustard and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over potato mixture; stir to coat.
Chill.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add apples, flour, baking soda and spices.
Mix all in a bowl.
Electric mixer not needed.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves or Bundt cake.

title: lemon-thyme pesto
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients in food processor, gradually adding the olive oil.
Process until smooth.
If pesto is dry, add more oil by spoonfuls.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Terrific over shrimp, pasta or salad.

title: quick chicken and rice
directions: In a saucepan, combine the soups and milk.
Heat thoroughly. Add rice and pour in a lightly greased baking dish.
Top with chicken and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: easy new england clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook and stir the bacon and onion until the bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Stir in soup and milk.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Stir in clams and liquor, lemon juice and pepper.
Heat through.
Serve with saltines.
Serves 4.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spam and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Melt margarine in a saucepan and add tomato sauce, onion, salt, paprika and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Add Spam and 3/4 cup of the cheese.
Heat until cheese melts. Stir in cooked drained macaroni.
Pour into a 2-quart pan or dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Night before:
Butter angel food cake pan. Dump in frozen rolls.
Blend dry pudding, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Scatter over dough.
Cut butter into pats and arrange over top of pan. Cover with foil and leave on counter overnight.

title: peanut butter candy(tastes like reese's cups)
directions: Melt margarine; mix all ingredients together except chocolate chips.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
Chill; cut into squares.

title: bean dip
directions: Put beans through colander.
Add enough mayonnaise for desired consistency.
Add jalapeno pepper, garlic salt, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce to taste.

title: old south sweet potatoes with caramel sauce
directions: After creaming	potatoes, add sugar, vanilla and cream. Put in greased casserole
dish,
make a well in the center and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake	at 350° until hot and just before serving, pour sauce over, filling the well.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain and chop.
Cream together cream cheese and mushroom soup in large mixing bowl.
Add spinach and cracker crumbs.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: midwestern barbecue (crock-pot)
directions: Put half of onions in crock-pot, then add meat, cloves, water and remaining onions.
Cover and cook overnight or 8 to 12 hours on low.
Remove bone and fat from meat; drain.
Put meat back into crock-pot.
Add chopped onion and barbecue sauce.
Cover and cook additional 1 to 3 hours on high or 4 to 8 hours on low, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Serve on large buns.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage, brown and drain.
Line a greased 13 x 9-inch pan with rolls and mash.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese. Combine other ingredients and beat well.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in bag. Shake biscuits in mixture.
Melt brown sugar and margarine and let boil 1 minute.

title: ting-a-lings candy
directions: Cream together the margarine, eggs, sugar and flavoring.
Sift the flour, include the baking powder.
Sift one more time. Gradually add flour to margarine, eggs and sugar.
Mix. Add milk, a little at a time.
Add raisins.
Grease a Bundt cake pan very well. Dust with flour all around.
Shake out any excess flour.
Add mix to pan slowly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Insert a toothpick, to make sure it is baked through.
Let the cake cool in the pan for 15 minutes on a rack!
Then invert the pan and put cake on plate. Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.
Makes 16 slices.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Mix cake and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan as directed; cool.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Mix all the ingredients thoroughly.
Add tears of sorrow and sympathy.
Flavor with gifts of love.
After pouring all this in your daily life, fold in 4 cups of prayer.
Serve with a smile at any time and it will satisfy the hunger of starved souls.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add pineapple juice, pineapple and lemonade.
Mix and chill.
Before serving, add bananas and ginger ale.

title: tacos
directions: Scramble hamburg until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add onion, taco seasoning and taco sauce.
Mix and simmer for 15 minutes.
Heat shells in oven at 200° for 10 minutes or until soft.
Fill shells with mixture.

title: chocolate almond gateau
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water, 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate morsels; stir until smooth.
Set aside. In a large bowl, combine sugar and butter; beat until creamy. Beat in melted morsels, egg yolks, vanilla and salt.
Gradually add flour and milk; beat well.
Stir in almonds.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Combine eggs, milk, vanilla and salt until thoroughly blended. Gradually beat in milk.
Gently fold in whipped cream.
Pour in a punch bowl and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, spices and salt.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients together and add the dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 coffee cans, bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: grandma erickson's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add sugars.
Beat eggs and add to butter and sugar along with vanilla.
Add dry ingredients followed by chocolate chips and walnuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Makes about 4 dozen medium sized cookies.

title: beef and squash casserole
directions: Drain cooked squash.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Add to cooked rice.
Season with salt and pepper.
Make
a sauce with milk, margarine, flour and one cup of the grated cheese.
Mix the sauce with the squash and meat mixture.
Place in casserole dish. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chips in large pan.
Add Crispix cereal.
Mix well.
Put in large, plastic bags and add confectioners sugar.
Shake well to coat.
Pour on cookie sheet to dry.

title: tuna noodle bake
directions: Blend butter and flour in heavy saucepan.
Stir in milk gradually.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in salt, Tabasco, Worcestershire, onion and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Layer broccoli and tuna in buttered casserole dish. Spoon cheese sauce over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Per serving: 380 calories, 20 g. protein, 13.4 g. carbohydrates, 83.3 mg cholesterol, 423 mg potassium, 27.9 g. fat and 929.3 mg sodium.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar, vegetable oil, eggs and pumpkin together. Sift and add all other ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins if desired.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans or one Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Spread beans with chilies on serving plate.
Mix together sour cream and taco seasoning; spread on top of beans.
Mash up avocados and mix with seasoned salt, garlic salt and lemon juice. Spread on top.
Chill several hours.
Garnish with sliced olives, shredded cheese, chopped green onions and chopped tomatoes. Serve with chips.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until browned; drain off fat.
In a saucepan, melt the 1/4 cup margarine.
Stir in flour and salt. Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in cooked sausage, sliced eggs and drained corn.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Toss bread crumbs with melted margarine; sprinkle atop casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: e-z peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix thoroughly the dry ingredients, then add vanilla, butter and milk.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add jar of Marshmallow Creme and jar of peanut butter; mix thoroughly.
Pour at once into a greased 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each one.
Add milk.
Crush wafers and add, mixing well.
Add pecans and coconut; mix well.
Grease and flour pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and serve.
(Do not add chips, ground beef and dressing until serving time.)

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream and mix first 4 ingredients, using egg yolks only.
Add extract and at low speed, beat in flour and milk alternately.
Add coconut.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Cool 15 minutes in pan before removing.
Sprinkle with 4x sugar or ice, if desired.

title: one bowl rocky road brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and butter in large bowl until butter is melted, approximately 2 minutes.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: butter cookies
directions: Bring margarine to room temperature and beat well.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat thoroughly. Fold in flour and beat well.
Roll in 1-inch balls and bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle liberally with powdered sugar while still warm.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup, tuna, salt and pepper.
Heat on stove until well mixed and hot.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Serve.

title: old-fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Melt sugar in a heavy skillet (iron works better).
Stir constantly until melted.
Stir in butter, baking soda, vanilla and peanuts.
Pour onto a large buttered platter quickly and spread with forks to the thickness desired.
It is very hot and thickens very fast.
Let cool and then break up into pieces.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cheez-Its crackers and oleo; spread in flat Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Top with Cheez-Its crackers.
Pour melted oleo over.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shells and sauce
directions: In large pan, pour olive oil and onion; simmer.
Add ground beef and sausage (brown).
Add tomato puree and tomato paste. Cook about 2 hours on low heat, covered.
Cook shells as directed. Drain; rinse with cold water.
In a large baking dish, alternate layers of sauce, cheese and shells.
Cover bottom of pan with sauce first.
End with sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: summertime potato salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, mustard, dill weed, salt and pepper to taste. Combine with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: apple dip
directions: *You may add more caramel extract to taste.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown beef lightly in butter.
Add vegetables and seasoning. Cook about 5 minutes in wok or heavy skillet.
Drain and cool. Place a heaping tablespoonful in middle of wrap.
Spread to half of roll.
Roll according to package.
Deep fry until lightly golden brown (2 to 3 minutes).
Serve with favorite seafood sauce (sweet and sour).

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 4 minutes.
Do not boil hard.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix well and drop onto wax paper by teaspoon.
Cool 1 hour.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: quick potato soup
directions: Bring hash browns, onions, chicken broth and water to a boil; heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in soups and milk and heat thoroughly.
Garnish with cheddar cheese or cooked ham or bacon. Makes a crock pot full.

title: baked rice dressing
directions: Mix ground meat with the raw rice.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery, onion tops and parsley.
Mix in soups and season with red and black pepper.
Put into heavy casserole dish with close fitting cover in order to retain all the juice.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: tortilla fingers(appetizer)
directions: Blend all ingredients except tortillas with a mixer or food processor until smooth.
Spread mixture on tortillas and roll up. I usually cover and chill overnight.
Cut into one-inch pieces. Serve with picante sauce.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Add margarine.
Add to bread cubes.
Add raisins. Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Mix together with milk and margarine.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into loaf pan.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: skillet barbecue chicken
directions: In skillet, saute chicken in oil.
Add barbecue sauce, 1 1/2 cups water and corn.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat.
Let set 5 minutes.
Stir.
Salt to taste.
Can add more barbecue sauce, if needed.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Heat chips and oil on Medium-high for 2 minutes in microwave.
Stir once, then microwave on High for 10 seconds and stir.
Pour over cereal; mix and stir until smooth.
Spread on three waxed paper lined baking sheets.
Cool.
Break apart.
Store in airtight container.

title: festive cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and pineapple with juice.
Mix well and mold.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix
eggs
and	1 cup sugar.
Add pumpkin, lemon juice, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
When smooth, beat in 3/4 cup flour and 1 teaspoon baking powder.

title: coney island hot dog sauce
directions: Fry ground beef and onion until brown.
Let cool.
Put in blender until fine.
Then add ketchup, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine and simmer 1 hour.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: baked chicken with sauce
directions: Dip chicken in 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Then roll in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in 13x9x2 inch pan. Put chicken in pan, skin side down and bake uncovered at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake another 15 minutes. Blend remaining buttermilk and soup; pour over chicken.
Bake 15 minutes more or until tender.

title: rice pilau
directions: In heavy skillet, heat and stir sugar until it browns and melts, being careful not to let it burn.
Add chicken, turning to coat with melted sugar.
Brown slightly.
Add rice, onion and seasoning, stirring a little.
Add water to cover.
Simmer, uncovered, until rice is cooked, adding water as needed.
Let boil dry at the end.
Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour vegetables
directions: In wok or large skillet, heat oil and stir-fry carrots, pea pods, green pepper and onion until tender, about 4 to 5 minutes. Add tomato, water chestnuts and cucumbers slices and cook a few minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel the avocado.
Cut avocado into cubes, about 3 cups.
Put the avocado into a mixing bowl and cut it back and forth with a knife to make a coarse mixture.
Add the other ingredients. Chill.

title: caramel pudding
directions: Caramel together butter, cream and sugar until real dark; turn off heat and add 5 quarts milk.
Let caramel melt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook like cornstarch.

title: lush cake
directions: Cut margarine into flour until it is like pie crust mixture. Add nuts and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Blend 1 cup sugar in cream cheese which has been at room temperature.
Blend in Cool Whip and mix with electric mixer until well blended.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cooled crust.
Mix instant pudding and milk and beat until thick.
Add on top of cheese layer.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut in squares.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Cook carrots and onion in boiling salted water for 15 minutes. Drain reserving 2 cups of cooking water.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour; gradually add cooking water, stirring until thick and smooth.
Let boil for 2 minutes; remove from heat. Stir in cheese until melted.
Arrange vegetables in casserole. Pour sauce over vegetables.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: lori's sauerbraten
directions: Bring vinegar, water, spices, salt and sugar to boil.
Cool. Pour over uncooked meat and let it stand in covered plastic or crock-pot in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.

title: tostones(fried green plantains)
directions: To remove the skin form the plantain, cut tips at both ends, cut a slit along the length of the plantain and peel off.
To facilitate easier handling, some cooks dip plantains in hot water for 5 minutes and then remove the skin.
Once plantains are peeled, cut into diagonal slices, about 1-inch thick.
Reserve peels: typically the unbroken skin of the plantain is used for flattening the tostones.

title: favorite banana bread
directions: Combine the cream cheese, sugar and margarine, mixing until well blended.
Blend in banana and eggs.
Add combined remaining ingredients, mixing until just moistened.
Pour into greased and floured (9 x 5-inch) baking loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: recipe for a happy day
directions: Measure words carefully.
Add heaping cups of understanding. Use generous amounts of time and patience.
Cook with gas on the front burner.
Keep temperature low; do not boil.
Add dash of humor and a pinch of warm personality.
Serve individually.

title: baked swordfish
directions: Mix last four ingredients well.
Marinate fish 1/2 hour in refrigerator.
Bake in 400° oven 6 to 8 minutes per 1/2 inch. Baste halfway through with remaining marinade.
No need to turn fish.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Blend oleo, molasses, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift together and add the rest of the ingredients to the oleo mixture. Refrigerate the dough for several hours.
Make off into small balls; roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° until firm or brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Fry hamburger.
Drain.
Add marinara sauce.
Heat to a boil. In Pyrex dish, layer sauce, noodles (do not boil noodles), cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Repeat 3 layers.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese in a mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add pudding mix and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Sprinkle 1/2 the crushed Oreos on top.

title: rural salad
directions: Peel tomatoes, if desired, and slice thinly. With tines of fork, score cucumbers lengthwise and slice thinly. In shallow bowl, arrange layers of tomatoes and cucumbers; sprinkle with cheese and olives. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over all. Chill before serving. If a tangier dressing is desired, add 2 to 4 teaspoons of lemon juice or wine vinegar to the oil, basil and pepper mixture. Makes 8 servings.

title: sandra's rolled sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir together flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Beat butter and shortening for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well combined.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Working with 1/2 of the dough at a time, on a lightly floured surface, roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 minutes or until done.
Makes 36 to 48.
Dough can be frozen and used later.

title: brocc-cheese-rice casserole
directions: Saute the onion, green pepper and celery in margarine until tender. Add soup, cheese and broccoli. Add rice and mix well. Place in 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. (Add mushrooms, if you wish.)

title: green beans supreme
directions: Simmer onion
slices
in
cup
of the butter until clear, but not
brown.
Arrange
half
of	the beans that have been drained
in
bottom
of
buttered casserole dish.
Spread half of mushroom
soup
and
onions on top of beans, then fill with remaining beans,
onions
and
soup.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Brown bread
crumbs
in rest of butter and spread on top of the casserole.	Bake
10 more minutes until crumbs are hot and slightly browned.

title: snappy tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and bake in a casserole for 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Easy but very good.

title: currant cakes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and chill overnight.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll each out thicker than pie crust into a rectangle.
Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and 1/3 box currants across each piece of dough, then dot each roll with butter.
Roll like a jelly roll. Flatten a little across top of roll with rolling pin. Bake at 350° to 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Do not grease pan.

title: pasta sauce with hamburger(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, bring to boil and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as per package instructions.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix, vanilla, buttermilk, coloring, margarine and eggs.
Blend until moist.
Add soda and vinegar.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in two 9-inch greased and floured pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with your favorite cream cheese frosting.

title: heritage chocolate cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa on low until smooth and thickened.
Pour into small bowl and cool.
Add vanilla.
Add sugar and milk alternately until desired consistency.

title: cherry cheese cream pie
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk; stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into shell and chill for 3 hours.

title: coconut pie surprises
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick and margarine in blender for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased pie pan; let stand 5 minutes. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Leave in oven for 5 minutes longer.
Remove and let cool.

title: easy fajitas(fa-he-tas)
directions: Cut meat into cube-size pieces.
Cook in large skillet (or wok) in oil with garlic and all spices about 10 minutes.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Cover and let cook about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and salsa.
Cover and let cook until meat and all veggies are tender (another 5 to 10 minutes).
Stir occasionally.
Serve with warm tortillas, sour cream and salsa.

title: ranch-style chicken
directions: Mix soup, broth, chili powder and peppers together;
simmer until hot and soup is completely melted. Add deboned chicken. Place Doritos chips in casserole dish and pour mixture over chips. Top with cheese and bake in oven until cheese melts. Serve hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and tear from bone. Mix soups, milk and sour cream. Mix butter and broth separate. Put half of the stuffing mix and cover bottom of 9 x 12 pan. Pour a little melted butter and broth over it, then take half of the chicken and put over dressing, then a layer of soups, milk, sour cream ingredients. Keep layering until used all and last, use remaining of dressing mix. Pour over remaining broth and butter. Put in oven with cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Make taco mix according to package.
Layer in casserole bowl the ground beef, Ro-Tel, sour cream and chili beans.
Shred or slice cheese to cover top and add chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until casserole is bubbly. Serve with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes.

title: guacamole
directions: Chop onion and tomato into tiny pieces and set aside.
Scoop the insides of the avocado into a bowl, keeping one pit aside.

title: western brunch
directions: Pour over filling; let stand 12 hours.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Arrange cookie slices on lightly greased baking pan, beginning 1/4 inch from groove of pan.
Continue to arrange in circular pattern, slightly overlapping.
Press lightly together to seal.
Place baking pan in oven.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Crust is done when edges just begin to brown; top of crust will not be browned.

title: hawaiian drop cookies
directions: Cream butter or oleo.
Add sugar, eggs and flour. Mix well. Add pineapple and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until edges start to turn brown.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Add salt and pepper to bread crumbs.
Beat egg and add milk. Dip chops in liquid and roll in crumbs.
Put 3 tablespoons of fat into skillet and brown chops.
Place chops in a baking pan or dish and add boiling water.
Cover and bake at 400° for about 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt. Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Will not spread while baking. Bake for 20 minutes or until edges are golden.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 18 cookies.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and soda; set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, vinegar and vanilla; stir.
Add dry ingredients; whisk until well blended. Pour into 2 (8-inch) round pans or 1 (10-inch) square pan.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Cool; frost with Coconut Pecan Icing.

title: rice krispies crust
directions: Mix ingredients and press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Freeze.
Fill with ice cream or chocolate mousse.

title: berliner kranse
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Mix all egg yolks until smooth.
A small amount of egg white may be added to egg yolk mixture.
Add the egg mixture to the sugar and butter and blend well.
Add the flour gradually as you may not need the full amount and you don't want the dough too stiff or it will not roll out well.
Work the flour into your cookie mixture with your hands. They work better than a spoon.
Take a small portion of dough and roll it into the size and length of a pencil.
Cross one end over the other end of dough to form a wreath.
Dip the wreath into raw egg white and then into sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° to 350° for about 20 minutes or until golden or lightly browned.

title: hershey brownies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; add eggs, chocolate, flour and nuts.
Beat well.
Bake in jelly roll pan for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: candy korn
directions: Remove all the unpopped kernels from the bowl.
Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, to 212° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light caramel color or 290°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour over corn and nuts. Toss with 2 spoons until corn is dry.
Break apart and spread on aluminum foil.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: In a bowl, combine rice, 1/4 cup egg substitute, and half of the cheese; mix well.
Pat into the bottom and up sides of a 9 inch pie plate coated with non stick cooking spray, set aside.
In another bowl, combine broccoli, mushrooms, milk, margarine, and remaining egg substitute.
Pour into crust.
Bake, uncovered, at 375 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Return to the oven until cheese melts.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: val's frozen daiquiris
directions: Combine and mix in blender.
Mix with crushed ice (12 ice cubes).
May add 1 package frozen strawberries.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a square 8-inch baking dish.
Cook and stir ground beef until brown.
Stir sour cream, mayo, cheese and onion; set aside.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Pat in pan, pressing dough 1/2-inch up sides.
Layer beef, tomatoes and green peppers in pan.
Spoon sour cream mixture over top.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crust from 6 slices of bread.
Butter bread and cut into strips.
Line large casserole dish with bread.
Brown 1 lb. sausage.
Drain well on paper towel.
Spread over bread.
Grate cheese, sprinkle over sausage.
Beat eggs with milk, salt, pepper, and dry mustard.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Let sit in refrigerator 8 hours at least before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be frozen after setting for 8 hours. before cooking.

title: aunt chris' two layer cheesecake
directions: Mix and line pan and sides.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Dip zucchini in batter to coat.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and syrup.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients mixing well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: friendship cake
directions: Cream greeting and smiles thoroughly.
Add handshakes separately; add love slowly.
Sift in hospitality and fold in interest in others carefully.
Bake in a moderate oven; serve warm to all new acquaintances.

title: potato supreme
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in water in saucepan, covered.
Simmer until tender.
Drain water and cool potatoes.
Peel and coarsely shred.
Mix cheese and melted margarine.
Add potatoes and mix. Add onions and season with salt and pepper.
Fold in sour cream. Pour into a greased baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
(May be made ahead and frozen before baking.)
When ready to use, remove from the freezer, thawed and baked as directed.

title: pennsylvania dutch funnel cake
directions: In a small bowl, whisk eggs to frothy.
Gradually beat in milk.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat smooth. Put 1-inch of oil in large skillet and heat. Put part of batter in a funnel, holding the bottom with finger.
Then hold over the oil and make a lacy pattern, starting in center.
Fry until golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels or brown paper.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve immediately while warm.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare pie crust for 1-crust pie; use to line 9-inch pie pan. Make high stand-up edge.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Pour pumpkin mixture evenly into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake about 45 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack about 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: creamed dried beef(breakfast)
directions: Melt butter in a large frypan.
Add beef.
Saute for about 5 minutes on medium heat.
Add flour and mix.
Slowly add half and half, soup and chicken broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
If mixture is too thick, add some more half and half.
Heat through. Serve over toasted English muffins for breakfast.
Very good over baked potatoes for dinner.

title: sunny mom's chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into lightly greased casserole(s).
Bake at 400° about 1 hour, until hot and bubbly.
Serve with tossed salad and garlic bread.
Makes enough for 2 meals for small family or 1 meal for large family.
Freezes well.

title: cheese fondue
