directions: Scald milk; add butter, cheese, salt and pepper and mix well. Turn oven to 350°.
Separate eggs; beat whites and yolks until thick.
Slowly add yolks to cheese sauce and fold in egg whites and bread crumbs.
Pour into ungreased baking dish and bake for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Follow directions for stuffing mix.
Add cream of mushroom soup and water to mix.
Layer the pork chops in 9 x 13 pan.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
tags: Stove Top stuffing mix for pork

title: little sausages
directions: Mix all ingredients (except Smok-Y-Links) over medium heat in saucepan until well mixed.
Cut Smok-Y-Links into fourths.
Pour sauce and Smok-Y-Links into bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Put in crock-pot on low until hot.
(Can use fondue pot on low.)

title: rice-a-roni medley
directions: Stir-fry sirloin strips in oil until cooked.
Set aside. Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions along with the rice, water, mushrooms and soy sauce.
When the Rice-A-Roni is cooked, add the meat and whatever cooked vegetables you like. Reheat until meat and vegetables are warmed.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Let all ingredients except chicken come to a boil.
Add chicken and pour into 3-quart casserole dish lined with crust.
Put top crust on and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: left over turkey casserole
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/3 cup hot water.
Add to rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole dish (uncovered) for 45 minutes at 350°.
Stir once or twice.

title: banana orange nutmeg bread
directions: Mix juice and bananas.
Cream margarine and sugar; add egg and banana mix.
Stir in flour, nutmeg, baking powder and soda.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in well-greased loaf pan.

title: strawberry whipped cream pie
directions: Combine crackers, egg whites and vanilla.
Press into a greased pie plate and cook at 350° until light brown.
Let cool.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add oil, milk and eggs. Then add prunes and vanilla. Add nuts. Beat 2 minutes. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place all ingredients in a casserole dish; do not blend together until after cooking in microwave for 2 minutes.
After 2 minutes in the microwave, mix well.
Add nuts, place on waxed paper and place in the freezer for 1 hour.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 round cake pans according to directions.
Cool and refrigerate to chill.
Cut 1 layer into small pieces and place in punch bowl.
Mix pudding according to package.
Spread 1/2 pudding on top of cake.
Add 1/2 berries; layer 1/2 of pineapple (drained) on top and add 1 sliced banana.
Repeat with other cake layer, ending with whipped topping.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the pecans in a 10-inch Bundt pan sprayed with Pam; set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Cut each biscuit in half; roll each one in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Layer in the pan.
Put other half of pecans on top.
Combine brown sugar into melted margarine.
(Boil 1 minute.)
Pour over top of the raw biscuits.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in the pan, then invert onto a platter. Serve warm.

title: non-alcoholic sangria
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients in a non-aluminum 4-quart bowl.
Add fruit and cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
Makes 10 cups.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground meat, onion, celery, garlic, mushrooms and salt together.
Drain grease off.
Place creamed corn and any other vegetables desired in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Add the ground meat mixture as the next layer.
Spoon the mashed potatoes on as the last layer.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, parsley flakes, chives and dot with butter.
Bake until brown, approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio pudding and cool whip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350 degrees. Serve warm.

title: french toast sandwiches
directions: Slice bread 1/2-inch thick, then butter.
Make sandwiches. Dip in batter; fry until brown in oil.

title: pumpkin nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Fold in 1/2 cup chopped walnuts or pecans.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add onion, seasonings and rice, stirring constantly until rice is slightly browned.
Pour rice into large casserole which has been sprayed with Pam.
Cook chicken in saucepan until almost done, then place it on top of rice.
Add broth plus enough water to equal 2 cups.
Cover and bake 20 to 30 minutes or until broth is absorbed.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour in pan over oleo.
Bake at 375° for 35 or 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baby orange cakes
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on package.
Place well-greased paper cup (hot drink cups) on a baking sheet.
Spoon in batter filling cups 1/2 full.
Bake in a moderate oven about 375° for 25 minutes.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown first three ingredients.
Add all other ingredients. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Use whatever kind of fruit you choose or fresh fruit, sweetened to your liking equal to 1 large can.
Melt oleo in 9 x 12-inch baking pan or dish.
Bring fruit to a boil.
Mix ingredients. Pour over melted oleo.
Pour hot fruit on next.
Bake at 350° until light brown or how you like it.

title: christmas eve punch
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; chill.
To serve, add ginger ale, stirring well.
Yield: About 4 1/2 quarts.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into butter alternately with eggnog, mixing only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in pecans, raisins and cherries.
Spoon into greased (with Pam) 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Dissolve yeast in 1 tablespoon warm water. Add other ingredients. Knead down and let rise once. Divide dough into 3 balls. Roll round and thin as pie crust. Spread with butter; cut as pie. Roll each piece, starting from outer edge to point. Place far enough apart on pan so as not to touch when they rise. Let rise. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°. Brush with butter when removed from oven.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. In yet another bowl, combine pumpkin and milk.
Add flour mixture and pumpkin mixture alternately to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Makes about 2 dozen.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: impossible quiche
directions: If using chopped ham, add chopped green pepper and onion to taste.
If using bacon, crumble and add chopped mushrooms. Sprinkle over bottom of greased quiche dish or pie plate.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chill 6 hours or overnight;
mix before serving.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour and milk to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: reuben balls
directions: Mix corned beef, sauerkraut (after well drained) and cream cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll mixture into walnut size balls.
Dip balls into beaten eggs and roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Put on paper towel to drip.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat thoroughly.
Pack into a loaf pan. Pour one 8 ounce can tomato sauce over all and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lynn swann cake
directions: In Bundt pan, mix cake mix and pudding dry.
Fold in sour cream, eggs, oil and water.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: barbara bush's zucchini soup
directions: Chop unpeeled zucchini, shallots and garlic.
Melt butter or margarine in a heavy frying pan.
Add chopped vegetables.
Cook for 10 to 20 minutes (stir to keep from burning; you don't want it to brown). Put all ingredients except for table cream into blender and blend.
Add table cream and blend.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Combine bacon drippings and flour in a large Dutch oven; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 10 to 15 minutes or until roux is the color of copper penny.
Stir in onion, celery and garlic; cook 5 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer over medium heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp, crabmeat and okra.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add oysters, if desired, and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Yields 4 1/2 quarts.

title: it's a mad cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour pineapple with juice in pan, then sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mixture.
Melt butter or margarine and pour over pecans.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Cherry pie filling or apple pie filling may be substituted for crushed pineapple.

title: pizza waffles
directions: Mix tomato sauce, cheese, 1 teaspoon oregano and 1/4 cup of water in 1-quart saucepan.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted and sauce is bubbly.

title: blueberry smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender. Blend for about 1 minute. Makes 1 large glass.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until brown or until knife comes out clean.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
In a deep bowl, arrange layers of carrots, onion and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients in pan and bring to a boil, stirring until well blended.
Pour over carrots and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Melt margarine.
Add onions and broccoli until broccoli is thawed.
Remove from heat. Add rice, cheese, soup and milk; mix well.
Cook 1 hour at 250°, covered.

title: cranberry salad(easy)
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into desired container and congeal.

title: oreo dessert
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine. Mix well. Add Cool Whip and mix well. In larger bowl, combine pudding, milk and vanilla; mix until thickened. Add cream cheese mixture to the pudding mixture. Crush cookies and spread half the bag on the bottom of 13 x 9 baking dish. Spread evenly. Spoon mixture on top of the Oreos and spread evenly, carefully not mixing cookies into the pudding mixture. Top with remaining crushed Oreos. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Must be kept refrigerated.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat tomato soup.
Soften Knox gelatine in hot water.
Pour soup and gelatine into bowl and add mayonnaise and softened cream cheese. Mix well with electric mixer.
Add diced vegetables and shrimp.
Stir well and pour into bowl or mold.
Chill 3 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Put can of cherries in bottom of rectangular cake pan and even out.
Drain pineapple juice from can.
Put pineapple evenly on top of cherries.
Dump cake mix (dry) on top.
Even out.
Place pads of butter all over the top about every 2 inches.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: old south cucumber lime pickles
directions: Mix pickling lime with water.
Soak cucumbers for 24 hours, stirring occasionally in lime water.
Soak in crockery, enamelware, or plastic (not aluminum pans).
Remove from lime water and rinse in 3 cool waters.
Soak 3 additional hours in ice and water. Remove carefully to drain.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Allow chicken to bake for 10 minutes, then flip and rotate chicken breasts.
Season as desired and pour cooking wine over the breasts.
Allow to cook for another 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: tasty baked salmon
directions: Drain salmon.
Place in 9-inch pie dish.
Pour sour cream over and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 450° until cream becomes thick and has a few brown patches.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Coat with flour.
Brown meat and onion in fat.
Add water.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours.
Add more water, if necessary.
Add potatoes and cook for 30 minutes, or until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Serves 6.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit well.
Mix in greased Pyrex dish, except bananas. Heat sugar, margarine and spices.
Cool, then add to fruit. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Add sliced bananas before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons brown sugar and nuts.
Return to oven 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: white chili(makes 6 servings)
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat until hot. Add onions and garlic; cook 20 minutes or until onions are golden; stir often. Add broth, beans, chilies, jalapeno peppers, lime juice, cilantro, oregano, cumin and cinnamon; bring to boil. Reduce heat to low and cook 20 minutes. Add meat and cook 10 more minutes or until heated through. Top with cheese and tomatoes.

title: peppers stuffed with corn
directions: Cut stems off peppers and remove seeds, then parboil for 2 minutes.
Combine and fill peppers.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Blend in Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze for about 3 hours before serving.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients; pour into a well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place sliced zucchini on top.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: potluck casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese. Put half of mixture in greased casserole dish.
Add 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Add rest of mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick dessert
directions: Make pudding according to directions on package.
Put milk in bowl.
Dip cookies in milk, then put in bottom of rectangular pan to form a crust.
Cover with pudding.
Cover pudding with Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Serve with fresh vegetables (pepper, cucumber, celery, cauliflower, etc.)

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
When tender, drain. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange glazed carrots and grapes
directions: Cook carrots according to package directions, omitting salt; set aside.
Combine the brown sugar, cornstarch, ginger and salt in a saucepan.
Gradually add orange juice, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Add carrots and grapes; cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: ruthie's chicken and ziti
directions: In frypan, saute scallion and garlic in olive oil (about 4 tablespoons).
Cut chicken in big chunks and saute in separate pan, oil and 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Cook chicken until juice runs clear.
Add scallion and garlic mixture, broccoli and red pepper; cook until al dente.
Serve hot with shredded Romano.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: When ready to serve, add slowly the 7-Up or ginger ale.
Mix in gallon jug as above.
Then finish filling jug with water. Stir.
Refrigerate.
When ready to pour into punch bowl, add 7-Up or ginger ale slow so as not to lose fizz.

title: chicken dish elegante
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put in oblong casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar to corn oil, beating well after each addition with an electric mixer at high speed.
Beat eggs until very light. Gradually beat, a little at a time, into the oil-sugar mixture; continue beating until mixture is smooth and fluffy.
Gradually stir in the sifted dry ingredients until thoroughly combined.
Add the carrots, nuts and pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch round cake pans (oil and line bottom).
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool on racks for 20 minutes before removing from pans. When cool, frost with cream cheese icing.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash and clean peppers.
Combine remaining ingredients except tomato soup and mix thoroughly.
Fill pepper shells lightly with meat mixture.
Place on rack in cooker; add soup.
Pressure cook at 15 pounds pressure for 10 minutes.
Reduce pressure.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together hamburg, sausage, pepper and salt.
Do not overmix.
Meat will get tough.
Saute onion and pepper.
Pour over meat.
Mix eggs, cracker crumbs and warm milk until moist.
Pour over meat.
Mix together.
Do not overmix.
Wet hands and roll loaf until slightly firm.
Let stand 1 hour.
Put foil in roaster and butter foil.
Put 1 cup water in roaster (outside of foil). Put loaf in foil.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Uncover.
Brown for 1 hour.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths, stir in jar of salsa.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican smothered chicken
directions: Cut up and deskin chicken.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and half bake the chicken at 350°.
In a large bowl, mix the soup and picante sauce.
Blend until smooth.
If mixture is thick, add a little milk until you get a medium thickness.
Drain grease off chicken and add mixture.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: lo-fat orange broiled chicken(heart healthy)
directions: Wash and dry chicken breasts; place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine other ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover; refrigerate 2 hours, basting occasionally.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Broil chicken until crisp and brown; turn to brown on second side. Meanwhile, heat marinade to serve hot over broiled chicken.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: thom's tossed salad
directions: Tear leaves off lettuce and put in bowl.
Quarter tomatoes and put in bowl with lettuce.
Toss.

title: buttermilk hot cakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add buttermilk and soda; beat again.
Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Add melted shortening.
Bake on heated griddle.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Blend the sugar, salt and half of vinegar.
Gradually add the oil, beating constantly with electric mixer.
Add remaining vinegar and celery seed.
Chill.
Excellent served over cut fruit such as apples, pineapple, bananas, etc.
Will keep in the refrigerator for days.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Add baking powder salt, sugar, and vanilla. Then add nuts and crackers. Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes, in a greased pan. Cover with whipped cream and place in refrigerator, until served.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, alternate flour and buttermilk.
Add eggs, soda, spices and cocoa.
Add jam.
Fold in raisins and nuts. Bake in layer pans at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: breaded veal chops
directions: Pound chops well.
Season with salt and pepper to taste then dust with flour.
Dip chops in egg and then in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot butter, turning when brown.
When done, put chops in oven to stay warm.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients for crust.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix butter, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Spread over cooled crust.
Peel bananas, dip in pineapple juice and layer on cake. Spread pineapple over bananas evenly.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix cornmeal, sugar, flour, salt, egg, hot pepper or green onions and hot water.
Drop 1 1/2-inch balls in oil (350°).
Brown about 1 minute.

title: zucchini with cheese and eggs(a family favorite)
directions: Heat oil and add chives or onion; saute until golden.
Add sliced zucchini, turning frequently until tender.
Add herbs to well beaten eggs and pour over zucchini.
Cook very slowly over medium heat without stirring eggs until set.
Sprinkle with cheese and slip under broiler to brown cheese lightly.
Cut in wedges and serve very hot.
(Chopped ham/bacon can be added to eggs.)

title: old fashioned pumpkin marmalade
directions: Peel pumpkin and cut in small cubes, discarding seeds and inner pulp.
Add sugar and let stand overnight.
Put lemons and orange through food grinder, discarding seeds, but reserving all juice.
Add to pumpkin.
Stir over low heat until boiling.
Simmer until thick and clear, about 3 hours.
Stir frequently to prevent scorching.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and process.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery; cook slowly 20 minutes.
Cook rice slowly in salted water; rinse in hot water 1 to 2 minutes, then drain.
Combine all ingredients plus 1/2 soup can water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: overnight breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain and	crumble.
Butter
x
9-inch pan. Tear white bread into bite-size pieces and layer in pan. Layer sausage over bread.
Combine
mustard,
milk
and
eggs. Pour over sausage.
Cover
and refrigerate overnight.
Combine cream of mushroom soup
and	milk.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg and add sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Add enough milk to make batter.
Peel a few apples and core the center.
Slice crosswise about 1/4-inch thick.
Dip in the batter and fry slow in an aluminum skillet.
Iron will get too hot and apples must be cooked soft pretty fast.
Cover to get done. Uncover to crisp.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Eat hot!

title: slop cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Cool. Prepare pudding as directed on package.
In large bowl or lid of Tupperware cake cover break up 1 cake, layer with 1/2 of the pudding, 1/2 of the Cool Whip and 1 Heath bar, repeat and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with tines of fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove cookies to cool completely.

title: party cheese log
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into log and roll in crushed pecans.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Heat and stir sugar, water and syrup in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage (235°).
Add nuts and salt.
Cook to hard crack stage (305°), stirring often.
Remove from heat; quickly stir in butter and soda.
Pour immediately into 2 well buttered 9-inch pans.
Spread with spatula.
Break into pieces when cool.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: franks-n-beans
directions: Fry cut-up wieners and add all ingredients; simmer 20 minutes. Pour in a baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° in oven until cheese is bubbly.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple in 8 1/2 x 11-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Slice butter evenly over cake mix; sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Add butter.
Boil until soft ball.
Add vanilla.
Add peanut butter.
Stir and pour in buttered pan.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put Ritz crackers over it. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press croissant dough into large 12 x 16-inch pan.
Cook as directed per croissant package and cool.
Mix room temperature cream cheese with dressing mix and mayonnaise.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with vegetables (ex.:
broccoli, cauliflower, red and green pepper, carrots, green onion, celery, Cheddar cheese or olives).

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: skillet franks and apple kraut
directions: Slice franks crosswise 8 times, cutting 3/4 of the way through.
In large skillet fry franks in butter until slightly browned and curved.
Remove and reserve.
Add onion rings to butter in skillet.
Saute until transparent.
Add applesauce, water and bouillon cube.
Simmer, stirring until cube dissolves. Add sauerkraut and celery seed.
Mix well.
Arrange franks on top of mixture and cover.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Combine the flour, soda and salt.
In large bowl, cream the margarine or butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well. Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before cutting in small squares.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Empty contents of beans.
Add brown sugar, smoke sauce, onion and barbecue sauce of your choice.
For added flavor, add bacon. Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.
After 1 hour, remove lid and stir contents.
Cover and bake one more hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix in a 2-quart dish the green beans, mushroom soup, salt, pepper and butter.
Top if off with the onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, Egg Beaters or egg whites, cocoa and applesauce or margarine until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in pan sprayed with Pam (9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
May dust with powdered sugar.

title: artichokes with garlic dip
directions: Using a sharp French chef knife, cut off and discard stems and tough bottom leaves of artichokes so they will sit upright.
Cut off one inch straight across the top of the artichokes.
Using scissors, trim the sharp tips off each leaf.

Rinse in cool water; drain and wrap individually in heavy-duty plastic wrap. Place each wrapped artichoke bottom side up in a custard cup. Rotating each cup and rearranging midway through cooking, microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix cornbread mix, egg and milk. Bake in an 8-inch square pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool and crumble. Combine tomatoes, pepper, onion, pickles and bacon. Toss gently.
Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice. Mix well. Layer half each of cornbread, tomato mixture and mayonnaise mixture in a large glass bowl. Repeat layers; cover and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Cook noodles; drain most of water. Mix all 3 cans together.
In a dish, layer noodles, meat and cheese.
Pour 1/2 of soup and Ro-Tel mixture over.
Layer again and pour other half of soup and Ro-Tel mixture.
Put in a 350° oven.
Top with cheese.
Cook until it bubbles.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Spread on the bottom of an oblong casserole dish.
Layer half of cheese on top of the sausage.
Beat eggs with seasonings and sour cream.
Pour over cheese and sausage.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° until set, about 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Cool.
Crumble into small pieces.
Combine eggs, cream, salt, pepper, sugar and nutmeg with hand beater.
Beat just enough to mix thoroughly. Sprinkle pie shell with cheese and bacon.
Pour in cream mixture. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven heat to 325°.
Bake 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: honey-orange glazed ham
directions: Carefully remove peel from orange in long strips.
Squeeze the orange, reserving juice.
For glaze, in a small bowl combine 2 tablespoons of the orange juice, the honey, cinnamon and cloves; mix well.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peach syrup into saucepan. Add the cloves and cinnamon. Stud peach halves with remaining cloves and return to peach can. Bring syrup to a boil; boil rapidly until reduced to about 1/2 cup.
Add brown sugar and vinegar. Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over peaches in can.
Let stand several hours; drain.
Can be used to garnish turkey, etc.

title: sherbet fruit twister
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 (1-cup) servings.

title: apricot bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
In a separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder. Gradually add to butter mixture.
Add coconut, walnuts and vanilla extract.
Mix thoroughly.
Press 2/3 of dough into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread with preserves.
Crumble remaining dough over preserves.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: sauerkraut and chicken
directions: Mix together all but sour cream in very large pan; make sure sauerkraut covers chicken and potatoes. Cover and cook over low medium for 1 1/4 hours at 350 degrees in oven. Stir occasionally. Serve directly from casserole with sour cream in separate bowl. Compliment dish with rye bread, butter and cold beer.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Mix melted margarine with sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift flour with baking powder; add alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Spread mixture in well buttered 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with ground cinnamon.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 30 minutes. Serve warm.

title: don's bread
directions: In large bowl, stir yeast and 1 tablespoon of sugar in warm water until dissolved.
Add remaining sugar, salt, milk, butter and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat on medium speed with mixer for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a workable dough, using all flour.
Knead 10 minutes.
Put in a greased bowl; cover and let rise 1 hour or double in size.
Push down.
Divide in half.
Let set 2 minutes.
Shape into loaves.
Put in pan.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: garden skillet
directions: Cook cauliflower in lightly salted water until tender (8 to 10 minutes).
Drain.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add zucchini, pepper and onion seasonings.
Cook until peppers are translucent. Add cauliflower; cook uncovered over medium heat, tossing occasionally until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes and cheese.
Remove from hat; toss until blended.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and confectioners sugar in a bowl.
Crush cranberry sauce with a fork; stir in lemon juice. Add to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts. Turn into an 8-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm.
Serve cut in squares on lettuce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix in cut vegetables and spices/dressing.
Toss lightly.
Chill overnight if possible, tossing occasionally.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel and cut up apples.
Slice bananas.
Add oranges.
Add 1/2 or 3/4 bag of marshmallows.
Add the sour cream.
Mix well and chill.

title: meat marinade
directions: Place all ingredients in blender jar and blend for 30-40 seconds.
Store tightly covered, in refrigerator.
Yields
3-1/3 cups.

title: bavarian kraut salad
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar about 5 minutes.
Let cool, then pour over other ingredients.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Toss together and serve.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over beets and let stand overnight.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and cauliflower; add chopped onions.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, garlic powder and salt and pepper.
Mix with vegetables and add peas.
Serve cold.

title: hot lettuce dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and add to heated bacon and grease.
Stir until evenly thickened and put over cold lettuce.
Serve.

title: tutti-frutti fruit salad
directions: Wash all fruits.
Cut in various shapes and sizes.
Amount depends on number serving.
Serve with toast and juice for breakfast; lunch with mixed greens and choice of meats/fish. Dinner appetizer or with ice cream for dessert.

title: yams
directions: Mix in a saucepan; cook until juice cooks down.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Cream margarine; add brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts to form crumbly mixture.
Remove 2 cups for topping.
Press remainder into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Blend sugar and cream cheese; add remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 18 to 20.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening, add brown sugar and stir until well mixed.
Allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, nuts, chocolate and vanilla.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Wipe beef with damp cloth.
Place in Dutch oven; cover with cold water.
Add onion, garlic, bay leaf and peppercorns.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Skim any foam; cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook approximately 3 hours or until meat is tender. Remove meat; keep warm.

title: summer casserole(serves 6)
directions: Peel eggs and cut lengthwise.
Arrange around edge of casserole dish.
Peel tomatoes, slice and put in center of dish. Make a white gravy of butter, salt, flour and milk.
Stir until smooth and medium thick.
Stir in cheese.
Pour this mixture over tomatoes and eggs.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Serve.

title: tuna dip
directions: Blend together until well mixed.
Serve with crackers.

title: christmas cordial
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon stick.
Bottle.
Add ice cube to each glass when served.

title: haystacks
directions: Heat chips until melted.
Stir noodles to coat evenly.
Drop by full tablespoonfuls on waxed paper and shape.

title: pickled okra
directions: Peel okra tightly in jars.
Put garlic cloves in each jar and pour boiling brine over okra in jar and seal. Hot water bath for 10 minutes in simmering water.
Let sit several weeks before opening.

title: peanut butter oatmeal candy
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and milk to a boil over medium heat. When it starts to boil, cook for 4 minutes stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed pepper.
Let cool.

title: chicken and rice delight
directions: Combine soups, rice and water in large casserole dish.
Place pieces of chicken on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° covered for one hour.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Continue cooking uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine sugar and milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, then cook without stirring to soft ball stage, about 232° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool to lukewarm.
Beat until thick and creamy.

title: italian baked mushrooms(a family recipe)
directions: Wipe mushrooms with wet paper towels. (Do not wash.) Slice thin.
Combine with next 7 ingredients.
Place in casserole and top with lemon slices.
Cover.

title: blender pecan pie
directions: Put eggs, sugar, salt, corn syrup, butter and vanilla extract in blender and blend well.
Add 1 c. pecans and blend just enough to chop nuts coarsely.
Pour into pie shells and place pecan halves on top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add margarine.
Put egg in a measuring cup and fill to 3/4 cup with milk.
Mix like a pie crust.
Divide in half and roll out.
Put half in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Fill with sliced apples, sugar and cinnamon. Cover with the other half of the crust. Bake about 50 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry-apple salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in boiling water.
Stir in whole cranberry sauce and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in chopped, unpeeled apple and celery; chill until firm.
Top with whipping cream mixed with mayonnaise.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften margarine.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake, uncovered, in a large baking dish for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cajun gingerbread
directions: With mixer cream together butter and sugar; add egg and molasses.
Mix until completely blended.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger, salt and cloves.
Add flour mixture and boiling water a little at a time to the butter sugar mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable beef dish
directions: Mix well all ingredients and bake in oven 1 hour or longer on moderate degrees (350°) or you may top with grated cheese if desired.

title: 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs, mix well. Pour into graham cracker pie crust. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: tropical dip for fruit
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cover and chill. Serve with assorted fresh fruit. Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: "bounty boudin"
directions: Place ground mixture in large pot and cover with water. Bring to	a
boil;
cover and simmer for 3 to 4 hours or until well cooked.
Pour
off	excess	liquid	and
reserve.
Grind onions, pepper,
celery
and garlic using grinder or blender. Mix
cooked meat
with ground vegetables and add cooked rice. Use 1
large bowl;
combine salt, pepper and Accent; mix well with other ingredients sampling at random to assure uniformity of seasoning. If too dry, add reserved meat liquid.
Fill hot casings
using either
a
sausage	stuffer
or a meat grinder attachment.	Twist casing every 6 to 10 inches (first flip to right, then
to	left) to make links.
Tie the ends.
To heat, place either
in
boiling water for 30 minutes or in microwave oven for 15 to 30 seconds. Freezes.
Makes a ton.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, oleo and sugar.
Then add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Then add rum flavoring and coconut flavoring.
Blend well.
Bake in an angel food cake pan at 325° for 1 hour, then check.
Do not check before 1 hour.

title: potato skins
directions: Cut strips from potatoes about 2 to 4-inches long and about 1 to 1 1/2-inches wide, leaving a little potato on the skin.
Place on cookie sheet and brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Brush with more butter and bake about 5 minutes more or until potato is tender and crisp.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Cut butter and add grated cheese, pepper and pimento. Combine all ingredients with beaten eggs.
Put in buttered casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 10 people.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Blend well.
Add flour, salt, sugar and baking soda which have been mixed well.
Add vanilla, chopped apples and raisins.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While cake is still hot, pur hot topping over in the pan.
Let cake cool.
When completely cool, remove cake from pan.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cut 4 ears of corn for whole kernel (about 2 cups).
Cut 8 ears of corn for cream-style (makes about 2 1/2 cups).
Mix together well.
Add cream, flour, salt and pepper.
Place in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: peanut butter ripple ice cream
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey, extract and nutmeg.
Layer ice cream and peanut butter mixture into metal bowl or other 2-quart freezer container, beginning and ending with the ice cream. Freeze until firm.
Scoop or spoon into serving dishes.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: dietetic applesauce cake
directions: Boil raisins and water until dry.
Beat oil and eggs together; add applesauce.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add to oil mixture.
Stir in raisins; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook and stir bacon and onion in 2-quart saucepan until bacon is crisp.
Add enough water, if necessary, to reserved clam liquid to measure 1 cup.
Stir clams, clam liquid, potatoes and pepper into onion mixture.

title: impossible broccoli pie
directions: Arrange broccoli in bottom of lightly greased 10x1-1/2-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat milk, baking mix, eggs and spices together about 15 seconds in blender (or 1 minute with hand mixer); pour into pie plate.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix the jello, boiling water and strawberries and refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Then break the cake into chunky pieces and drop into the jello.
Grease a large tube pan and pour the batter into it.
When thick, best if refrigerated overnight, invert on cake dish and ice with whipped cream topping.

title: fried soft crabs
directions: Clean and wash crabs; drain well.
Place breader mix and 3 crabs at a time in shaker bag.
Coat well and place in hot, deep fat.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add flour, cloves, cinnamon, soda and salt to first mixture.
Stir well.
Add grated apples and stir well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Add sugar and nuts sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients on low until margarine melts.
Keep warm. Stir well.

title: spiced sugared nuts
directions: Mix together in saucepan all ingredients.
Bring to boil and cook without stirring to 236° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add 1 quart shelled nut halves (pecans or walnuts).
Mix until all nuts are coated.
Turn out on waxed paper and separate the nut halves from mixture while still hot.
Let stand until cold.

title: marilyn's tamale dip
directions: Mix onions, tomatoes and tomato sauce in a saucepan. Simmer, covered, for 3 hours. Add tamales with sauce and all other ingredients. Top with cheese before serving.

title: fat-free popcorn treats
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving or early in the day, lightly coat a 6-quart Dutch oven, spoon and 13 x 9-inch baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Slice each piece of candy corn in half lengthwise.
In Dutch oven over very low heat, melt marshmallows, stirring constantly, with spoon.
Remove from heat.
Add popped corn, stirring to coat evenly.
Stir in candy corn.
Using waxed paper, press mixture evenly into pan.
Let cool about 1 hour.
Cut into 24 squares.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Combine squash, onion, egg, salt, pepper and flour in bowl; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Deep fry until brown; drain.
Serve hot.
Yield:
32 servings.

title: dieters' stew
directions: Brown meat; drain off all excess fat. Mix meat with remaining ingredients in a crock-pot.
Simmer until done.
Serves 8.
One serving equals 203 calories and 15 grams fat.

title: el pedregal's oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugars.
Add egg while mixing; add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg and add slowly to the sugar mixture. Stir in oats and raisins.
Use an ice cream scoop to shape dough into balls and place 3 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Press each down lightly and bake 13 minutes at 350°.
Makes 15 large cookies.
You can drop by tablespoon for a smaller cookie. Cooking time remains the same.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach until dry.
Stir together spinach, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add soup mix, water chestnuts, and onions.
Blend well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir before serving with any bread or cracker.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients
in blender and mix until frothy.

title: apricot cranberry bread
directions: Stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together in a large bowl.
Add apricots and cranberries.
Toss lightly until fruits are coated.
Beat eggs, milk, melted butter and lemon peel together in a small bowl.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then tip it out and finish cooling on cooling rack or bread board.

title: diet cauliflower salad
directions: Arrange in layers in order given in salad bowl.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: shahee dessert
directions: Mix the milk and half and half cream.
Add cardamom and food coloring (few drops) in it; let it boil on low heat for about 15 minutes.
Add sugar; let it cook over low heat.
Fry one slice of bread in deep fryer until it is brown.
Dip it in warm milk and remove it before it gets too soft.
Place it on a flat dish. Repeat the same process for the other slices.
Place the slices side by side on the same flat dish and pour some leftover milk over them.
Sprinkle dried milk powder over the slices.
Cool them in the fridge.

title: tater-tot casserole
directions: Chop
onion
and
cook in margarine.
Spread raw ground beef in
9 x 13-inch glass Pyrex dish; spread onion and cheese over meat.
Pour
soup over onion and cheese, then layer Tater Tots. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Ground turkey meat may be substituted for ground beef.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine mushrooms, onion, garlic and margarine in 2 quart casserole and cover.
Microwave at High until tender, 2 to 4 minutes.
Shake beef, flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag until beef is coated.
Stir beef and remaining ingredients except sour cream into vegetable mixture.
Microwave, covered, at High for 5 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium-high (70%).
Microwave until beef is tender, 20 to 30 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream until blended. Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tupperware pie crust
directions: Use large Tupperware mixing bowl and seal.
In regular Tupperware mixing bowl, mix first 2 ingredients.
Seal the bowl and shake.
Add shortening; seal and shake until it reaches cornmeal texture (approximately 2 minutes).
Add cold milk; seal and shake 30 to 45 seconds.
Lightly flour and chill before rolling out.

title: sweep steak
directions: Line baking dish with ample aluminum foil.
Place meat in center.
If desired, surround with veggies.
Sprinkle with onion soup.
Tightly wrap foil around meat.
Bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: energy pancakes
directions: In large bowl, combine egg and milk.
Add to egg mixture, oil and vanilla; blend well.
Mix in oats, raisins, sunflower and sesame seeds, wheat germ, bran and shredded apple.
Refrigerate overnight.
Batter will last about two weeks.

title: breakfast chocolate syrup
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour until well blended.
Stir in milk gradually and mix well.
Cook over medium heat until it thickens. It should be the consistency of medium white sauce. Stir in butter and vanilla.
Serve with hot homemade biscuits and butter. The more butter the better.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes in lightly greased pan.
When done, top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water and sugar.
Chill until set.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and bananas.
Let congeal in refrigerator and spread with topping.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Crush 1 1/2 cups Ritz crackers and
mix with 1 stick of melted margarine.	Use half of
crackers
in
bottom of casserole.
Saute onions and celery in
about
tablespoon of the melted margarine.	Mix ingredients well
and
pour into casserole.
Top with remaining cracker
crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: gaelic coffee
directions: Warm glasses.
Put 1 1/2 tsp. brown sugar in each glass and half fill with hot strong coffee, which dissolves the sugar. Quickly pour a good measure of whiskey into each glass and layer a little cream.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well, pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in 350 degree oven for 50 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix together and put into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes or until browned.
Cool.

title: easy-does-it pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and salt and stir until sugar is dissolved. Add cucumbers, peppers, onion and celery seed and put into containers.
Refrigerate for at least 1 day.

title: fresh green beans
directions: The amount of ingredients depends on how much you want. Slice green beans lengthways down the middle like French-style. Saut in a little water until almost tender. Add mushrooms. Cook until almost tender and water is cooked done. Add soy sauce and simmer about a minute.

title: three-day coconut cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix using package directions for 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Split layers into halves horizontally.
Mix coconut, sour cream and sugar in bowl.
Measure and reserve 1/2 cup coconut mixture.
Spread remaining coconut mixture between layers.
Mix reserved coconut mixture with whipped topping.
Spread over top and side of cake.
Chill, covered, for 3 days before serving. Yield:
12 servings.

title: turkey croquettes
directions: Melt butter; blend in
flour and gradually add milk and cook, stirring constantly until
thickened.
Add
a little hot mixture to egg and mix
well.
Stir into hot mixture and cook, stirring constantly one minute.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly. Chill
thoroughly.
Shape
into
croquettes
and arrange in greased shallow baking
dish.
Bake
at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 4.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and margarine. Combine milk mixture with dry ingredients.
Stir until barely mixed.
Spray nonstick frying pan or griddle with cooking spray or melt margarine in very hot pan/griddle, whichever you prefer. Pour batter into pan/griddle.
When air bubbles burst on top of pancake, turn.
Keep constant watch on pan/griddle; too hot will burn pancake and not cook centers evenly, too cool will either make pancake stick or cook unevenly.
Serve with pancake syrup, warmed in microwave, if desired.

title: oyster cracker surprise
directions: Place oyster crackers in a big Tupperware bowl.
Mix all the other ingredients with the oil and stir; then pour over oyster crackers and place in refrigerator, stirring once every 6 hours. Eat.

title: corn flake chewies
directions: Melt together white sugar, brown sugar and corn syrup.
Boil 1 minute. Add peanut butter and corn flakes. Mix and press into 7 x 11-inch pan. Cut into squares.

title: honey crunchers
directions: Mix and roll into balls.

title: spiced autumn fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add ginger ale.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a lightly oiled 8-inch square dish. Cover and chill until firm.
Makes 9 servings.

title: burrito supreme
directions: Warm tortillas on grill or in a skillet until slightly browned. Cook meat until done in skillet.
Spoon approximately 2 tablespoons meat into tortilla.
Add a heaping teaspoon of sour cream and guacamole inside tortilla.
Pour about 2 tablespoons red chile sauce over the folded stuffed tortilla.
Sprinkle lettuce, tomatoes, onion and cheese over red chile sauce.

title: homemade potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a large Dutch oven and cover with water. Bring to a boil.
Boil until potatoes are tender; remove from water and cool.
Slice potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add onion, garlic, celery and dill.
Toss to coat well.
Add mayonnaise, a few tablespoons at a time, until salad is mixed well.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring 3/4 cup of vinegar and 1 cup of sugar to a boil and pour over the other mixture.
Chill.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and salt in skillet.
Pour off excess grease.
Add enchilada sauce and soup to beef.
Layer tortilla strips and beef mixture in greased 10 x 10-inch baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: quickie hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat; pour off fat.
Combine meat, macaroni, tomato soup, mushroom soup and tomato sauce.
Sprinkle top with cheese (grated).
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 20 minutes.

title: brownies for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
If desired flour and add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Press 1/2 meat in small loaf pan.
Spread 2/3 of cheese over meat, leaving 1/2 inch bare around edges.
Place rest of meat on top of cheese, pressing edges to seal.
Bake for 35 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese; return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: southern fried turkey wings
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Wash turkey wings; cut in half and cut tip off.
Coat turkey with egg, then with flour mixture. Fry in hot oil in skillet on medium-high heat about 15 minutes, turning to brown evenly.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove cover.
Turn to medium-high and cook 10 minutes more, turning occasionally to crisp.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise and pineapple until creamy.
Then combine rest of ingredients.

title: bubble and squeak
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cook, drain and mash with milk and butter. Plunge cabbage into boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain and chop fine.
Combine with potatoes and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill for 2 or more hours.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned slightly.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients and mix until just mixed. Spread in 8X8 pan and bake at 375° for 20-25 minutes.

title: chicken with apricot sauce
directions: Mix preserves and dressing together.
Place chicken in long, Pyrex dish and pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with topping.

title: pecan fudge pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the first eight ingredients until smooth.
Stir in nuts; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.
Cool completely.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken-cornbread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients using enough chicken broth to moisten until very soft.
Pour into baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven until top browns.
Serve with chicken or turkey.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, softened cream cheese and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and place in oiled casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Will puff slightly.
Can be refrigerated or frozen and baked later.
Increase baking time accordingly.

title: cherry coconut cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture. Blend well.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cherry pie filling on top.
Sprinkle with coconut. Bake at 350° until cake tests done.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: brown bag snack beef rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef, onions and mushrooms in garlic salt, sage and butter.
Drain this mixture and place a tablespoon of mixture on each crescent roll triangle.
Sprinkle them with cheese; roll them up and bake about 10 minutes until brown.
A good snack; can be frozen and eaten the next day at room temperature.

title: orange drink
directions: This makes one gallon.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix
all
three ingredients
together
well.
Form into small 1-inch balls.
Place in baking dish and bake at 375° for 25 minutes, or until uniformly brown.	A broiler pan with rack works very
well, also.
Excess grease goes to bottom.
These make a great party food.

title: flu stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a casserole, raw meat and all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Measure 2 1/2 cups dry cake mix for topping.
Combine remaining dry mix, flour, yeast, water and eggs.
Beat 100 strokes by hand. Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with cherry filling evenly.
Mix reserved cake mix, 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and butter with fork until finely grained.
Spread over filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Combine crab meat and shrimp with vegetables which have been chopped very fine.	Add mayonnaise.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix	well.
Cover
with
bread
crumbs. Bake in moderate oven 30 minutes at 350°.

title: m&m monster cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients except M&M's and chips.
Scoop cookies out with ice cream dipper.
Making a firm ball, place on cookie sheet.
Bake 5 minutes, then put more M&M's on top.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes more.

title: teatime tassies
directions: Mix pastry dough with hands.
Roll into big ball.
Chill 1 hour.
Mix into 1 inch balls and press to fit small ungreased muffin tin.
(May spray lightly with Pam.)

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Beat eggs well; add milk and shortening.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add slowly to egg mixture, stirring well.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Thin batter slightly with cold water.
Spoon on hot griddle to form desired size.
Brown on each side for 1 to 2 minutes.
Yields 12 to 14 pancakes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix sugar, cake mix, oil and nectar slowly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let stand in pan until cool.
Ice while still warm.

title: date cake
directions: Finely chop the dates.
Put baking soda over dates and hot water.
When cool, add to following mixture:
Cream the butter; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine salt and flour.
Alternate flour mixture with dates and water, then add walnuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12 pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: gramma grace's chili (cinti style)
directions: Add all in large pot.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Well worth the wait!

title: holiday salad
directions: Soften cream cheese, then beat in mayonnaise and sugar.
Fold in pineapple, cherries, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator to set.
I normally make a double batch.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and onion.
Mix soups as directed and pour over potato mixtures.
Add spices.
Mix in cheese (I sometimes use partial soup, 1/2 can with 1/2 cup cheese).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix
together
and pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Cover with corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stella d'oro anginetti cream puffs
directions: *The cream puffs can be found in the cookie section of your local grocery store.

title: cheese snappy wafers
directions: Cut butter into flour until texture resembles coarse meal. Mix in cheese, cayenne and salt.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Pinch off small pieces, place on ungreased cookie sheet and pat flat. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix Kahlua, dry pudding and milk.
Layer cake, Kahlua mixture, Cool Whip and chopped bars of candy.
Alternate layers.
End with Cool Whip and crushed bars of candy.
tags: regular size chocolate instant pudding mix

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Thirty minutes before serving, mix in next 4 ingredients.
Immediately before serving, add the chow mein noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brunch scrambled eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place dough in ungreased casserole. Saute choice of vegetables in butter.
Set aside.
Lightly beat eggs.
Cook and scramble in additional butter.
Place eggs in unbaked crust.
Layer with vegetables and ham.
Top with cheese. Bake 15 to 17 minutes until brown and cheese bubbles.

title: lasagna
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain meat.
Add tomatoes and break up with fork.
Stir in tomato paste, garlic salt, oregano and basil.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir cottage cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan. Set aside 2 1/2 cups meat sauce.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, alternate layers of noodles, cheese and meat sauce.
Spread reserved meat sauce over top. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: In a 4 1/2-quart pot, boil potatoes.
Drain water and add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat until cheese melts. Garnish with chopped green onions.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into bite size balls.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18
minutes.

title: chocolate krispies
directions: Melt chocolate; add Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper or pour into candy bar molds.
Let cool until hard.
Store in airtight container.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Set aside.
Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs, blackberries and buttermilk mixture, mix well.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
Put in loaf or round cake pans.
Bake until tests done with a toothpick (approximately 60 minutes).

title: cold dough cakes
directions: Work flour and Crisco together until crumbly.
Add other ingredients.
Work dough until it forms a ball and leaves bowl clean.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight or for about 6 hours.

title: crunchy peanut butter candy
directions: Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove and stir in 2 cups peanut butter.
Pour over 3 cups corn flakes and Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoon on greased wax paper.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: In shallow dish, combine 1/2 cup soup and 1 cup milk.
Set aside.
On wax paper, lightly coat chicken with the flour, then dip in soup mixture.
On another piece of wax paper, dip chicken in stuffing on baking dish.
Place chicken then drizzle the rest of soup, oleo and lemon juice over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: mom's chicken
directions: Brown chicken in frying pan after coating with Frying Magic. Place water at the bottom of a baking casserole dish.
Chicken should be layered singly if possible.
Place chopped onions on top of chicken.
Cover with brown sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Break egg over apples and mix lightly.
Add sugar, oil, nuts, raisins and cinnamon, then add vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and salt and add to the above mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes, using a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: rice cereal
directions: Heat rice in saucepan with a little milk (to make it creamy) and sprinkle with brown sugar to taste.
Can also be done in microwave.

title: microwave fish fillets
directions: Put fillets into 10-inch pie plate.
Season with lemon juice and pepper.
Sprinkle with salt (if desired) after cooking.
One half-inch fillet will cook in 2 to 2 1/2 minutes on Full power or 2 fillets 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: very easy pie crust
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients into a 9-inch pie plate.
Add oil and milk and stir with a spoon.

title: zucchini burger italiano
directions: Cook zucchini, uncovered, 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain.
Cook meat, onions and garlic until meat is brown and onions transparent. Stir cooked rice, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano into meat mixture.
Combine egg, cottage cheese and shredded cheese.
Layer in casserole dish zucchini sprinkled with salt, meat mixture, cheese mixture and another layer of zucchini.
Sprinkle with salt. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese around edge.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, bacon bits and raisins together; let set overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together; let set, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Mix together; let set 30 minutes before serving.

title: oyster stew
directions: Cook seasonings in oyster liquid. Heat milk and butter or margarine; do not boil.
Combine all ingredients. Simmer until oysters curl at edges.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: low-fat chicken cacciatore
directions: Place cup up canned tomatoes (drained), tomato sauce, oregano, basil, honey and pepper in 3-quart saucepan.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Heat 4 tablespoons broth in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Stir-fry garlic, onion, green pepper and chicken for 10 minutes, until chicken is no longer pink inside. Add chicken and green peppers to sauce and simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Add peas and balsamic vinegar and cook uncovered an additional 5 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump all ingredients together and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Prepare icing in a saucepan by cooking together the sugar, margarine and evaporated milk for 10 minutes; do not boil.
Remove from heat and add nuts and coconut.
Spread over hot cake.

title: garlic butter
directions: Wrap garlic in aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes, or until garlic is very soft (like butter).
Spread on anything you desire.
Disney World reportedly adds it to butter or margarine to make a garlic spread for bread, potatoes, etc.

title: strawberry sauce
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Place in container of electric blender and process until smooth.
Add sugar and brandy; process until mixed.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: tailgate beans
directions: Cook beef and bacon until done and pour off fat. Saute the onion in bacon drippings. Combine all ingredients. Bake in casserole or large pan at 350° until bubbly (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: gingersnaps
directions: Sift together flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar, beat in eggs and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients over creamed mixture and blend well.
Form teaspoons of dough into balls and coat with granulated sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325°.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix white cake mix according to directions and bake as sheet cake.
Cream the cream cheese and set aside.
Mix pudding and milk; add cream cheese.
Fold into Cool Whip and spread on cooled cake.
Spread on layer of pineapple and top with layer of coconut.

title: french dressing from mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl until evenly distributed.
Put mixture in foil packet or 1-pint glass jar. Store in cool, dry place and use within 6 months.
Makes about 5 tablespoons mix, enough for 1 1/4 cups dressing.

title: mashed potatoes with cheese
directions: Mash potatoes.
Spread extra butter in casserole.
Mix all ingredients and put in casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
(If made in advance, bake for 1/2 hour.) Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet-n-smoky brisket
directions: Trim excess fat from brisket.
Poke holes in brisket with tip of knife or large fork.
Combine brown sugar and bottle of Claudes.
Mix until mixture is syrupy.
Spoon over brisket and rub into meat.
Sprinkle seasoned salt and pepper liberally onto top of brisket.
Wrap in foil.
Leave overnight in a cool place.
Cook at 350° for 3 to 4 hours or until doone.
Cook brisket with fat side up.
Do not turn over while cooking.
Slice meat with the grain while warm.

title: turkey and scalloped potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Pour potato slices into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with contents of seasoning mix envelope and turkey.
In a medium saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Stir in carrots, peas, milk and margarine; return to a boil.
Pour over potatoes; stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake an additional 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: golden fried shrimp
directions: Butterfly shrimp and wash under cold running water.
Combine eggs and salt in a shallow bowl.
Combine flour and cracker crumbs in flat pan.
Dip each shrimp in egg mixture, then roll in cracker mixture.
Repeat procedure.
Fry at 365° for 2 to 3 minutes, until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil hen for 1 hour or longer.
Salt it as you're boiling it. Keep the good, rich broth.
Mix all the remaining ingredients together, adding the broth slowly until it is a little mushy.
Salt and pepper to your taste.
Cook the pan of dressing for 30 minutes or more at 450°.
Put the chicken on top the last 10 minutes. Cooking time can depend on how mushy you make the dressing from the broth.
You don't want it to get too dry.

title: shrimp fettuccini
directions: Saute vegetables in butter for 15 minutes, covered.
Add flour and cook 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 15 minutes.
Add 1/2 Velveeta cheese (chopped) and cook until melted.
Add jalapeno pepper and cook 10 minutes.
Add half and half and cook until heated.
Season to taste.
Boil noodles and add to shrimp mixture. Put in a large, well greased casserole.
Top with rest of Velveeta and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, arrange potato slices.
Place browned pork chops over potatoes.
Combine soups, milk, onion, salt and pepper; mix well and cover pork chops.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover; bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until pork chops are tender.

title: spaghetti chicken
directions: Beat egg in bowl.
Mix crumbs, flakes and Parmesan cheese in separate bowl.
Dip chicken in egg.
Then in mix.
Arrange chicken over Prego sauce in baking dish.
Spoon some sauce over chicken. Bake covered for 1
hour at 400°.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake uncovered until cheese is melted.
Serve with spaghetti noodles.

title: spritz butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in egg, peel and vanilla.
Mix in flour and salt.
Use cookie press with desired shapes.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool; dip cooled cookies into chocolate and then into sprinkles.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: grandmother smith's no-fuss dinner rolls
directions: Mix salt, sugar and yeast in a very large bowl (large enough for dough to rise) and add 2 cups of lukewarm water.
Add half of the flour and mix in.
Add egg and mix.
Add melted butter.
Add remaining flour and mix quickly.
Cover with Saran Wrap and let rise 1 hour, until doubled its bulk.
Punch down and form into rolls.
Let rise again for about another hour.
Bake at 425° on greased cookie sheet for about 20 minutes.
This is a favorite at every family gathering.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix together cooked spaghetti, butter, Parmesan cheese, Cheddar cheese and beaten eggs.
Place mixture into a baking dish. Layer remaining ingredients in given order, ending with spaghetti sauce on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch glass dish, spread refried beans to cover bottom.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat; add soup mixture.
Layer in casserole dish as follows: Tater Tots, meat and soup, cheese and Tater Tots.
Salt and pepper to taste and add onion powder.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar, salt, margarine and raisins.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens (about 20 minutes).
Stir in vanilla.
Makes 2 servings.
(I usually double the recipe.)
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Chill.

title: our favorite fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and butter in a saucepan.
Stirring often, cook to 234° or until forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until thick.
Pour into greased
dish (8 x 13-inches) and refrigerate until firm, then cut.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: In one bowl beat cream cheese, egg, sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Add semi-sweet morsels.
In a separate bowl beat flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, 1/2 teaspoon salt, water, oil and vinegar. Fill muffin cup 1/3 full with second bowl and top with 1 teaspoon of the cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar on top (optional) and almonds (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: low cholesterol dip
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, beat cottage cheese on low speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Add mayonnaise, onion, white pepper, celery salt, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and hot pepper sauce.
Mix well.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 8 hours to let flavor blend.
Serve with fresh vegetables such as carrot, celery sticks, broccoli and cauliflower.

title: refrigerator fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk into a heavy pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until boils.
Turn heat down to prevent scorching.
Cook for 10 more minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately add chocolate pieces, syrup, butter and flavoring. Stir well until chocolate has melted and fudge is smooth and creamy.
Add nuts; mix until blended well.
Pour into unbuttered 8-inch pan surface.
Will set rapidly.
So spread quickly with spatula.
Chill 1 to 2 hours or until firm, cut into squares. Makes about 2 pounds to 2 1/2 pounds of candy.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle the rice in flat cake pan.
Pour over the rice, the soups and milk, which have been heated together.
Lay the cut up chicken over this.
Sprinkle the dry onion soup mix over all. Cover with foil; bake in a 325° oven for 2 1/4 hours.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat the whites until frothy.
Add salt and cream of tartar; continue beating until eggs are stiff.
Add the cornstarch to sugar and fold into egg whites, then fold the flour into the eggs, small amount at a time.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: pita crisps
directions: Heat the oven to 400°.
Combine the oil, cumin, cayenne pepper and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Split the pitas in half.
Brush the cut side of each half with the flavored oil.
Stack the pitas and cut them into quarters.
Spread them on a baking sheet in a single layer and bake until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Transfer to a rack to cool.
Fill with your favorite chopped meats and vegetables.

title: french pound cake
directions: Separate egg yolks and whites.
Cream the shortening and add sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and flour (a little at a time).
Add milk slowly.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in batter. Butter and flour tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: caramel layer squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler or in microwave.
In a large bowl, combine by hand rest of ingredients, except chips.
Stir until dough holds together. Press half of dough into pan and bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture on top of chips.
Spread remaining dough mixture over caramel and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Combine in 4-quart saucepan the sugar, raisins or substitute, raisins and candied fruit.
Add boiling water, cinnamon, salt and Crisco.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Chill thoroughly and add baking soda and water.
Mix well and add flour. Mix well and pour in 8 x 10-inch greased pan.
Bake at 300° about 1 hour.

title: freezer cucumber pickles
directions: Wash and brush cucumber and cut into slices.
(Do not peel.) Place cucumber, onion and pepper in plastic pan.
Sprinkle with salt; mix well.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Drain well and put into plastic containers.
Mix sugar and vinegar; heat to dissolve. Pour over cucumber mixture in containers.
Seal and freeze.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together.
Cook 20 minutes. Makes 9 1/2 pints.

title: macaroni fruit medley
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and set aside.
Cook egg, sugar, flour, salt and juice from can of crushed pineapple until thick.
Pour over macaroni and refrigerate overnight.

title: korean salad
directions: Toss the spinach with the bean sprouts.
Dice the hard-boiled eggs and fry; crumble the bacon and add to the vegetables along with the water chestnuts.
Combine the salad oil, sugar, catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and grated onion in a food processor to make the dressing.
Add salt to taste and mix with the vegetables.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown.
Drain and add seasoning and water, stirring well.
Boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine beans and half the taco sauce.
Spoon half of this into pie shell and top with half of the meat mixture, half the cheese, and all the chips.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400 degrees.
Cut into wedges and top with lettuce, tomato and remaining taco sauce.

title: egg and cheese casserole
directions: Fit 1/3 bread lightly into greased casserole.
Sprinkle 1/3 parsley, onion and grated cheese on top.
Make 2 more layers the same.
Beat eggs lightly and mix with milk, salt, pepper and mustard, worcestershire sauce.
Pour over bread in casserole.
Let stand 12 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Remove from refrigerator 2 hours before baking time and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 10-12 people.

title: straw-ba-nut ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer at medium speed until frothy. Gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Stir in condensed milk and vanilla.
Combine strawberries, bananas, and pecans.
