Fold in whipped topping.
Add fruit mixture to egg mixture; stir gently. Add food coloring if desired.
Pour into freezer can of 1 gallon freezer.
Add enough milk to fill can 3/4 full.
Let ripen at least one hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in bite size pieces and brown.
Mix together all other ingredients except onion and green peppers.
Add to meat and simmer 45 minutes.
Add onion and green peppers and simmer 30 minutes longer.
Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cut around core of cabbage.
Put in pot of boiling water; remove leaves as they soften and drain on a towel.
Wash sauerkraut and drain.
Saute onion in 1/3 cup oleo.
Put kraut on bottom of pan.
Mix all ingredients and salt and pepper to taste. Trim thick part of each leaf so you can roll it.
Use small amount of meat for each one.
Roll once, fold over one side, finish rolling and push end of cabbage into meat mixture.
Use leftover cabbage to put on top.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Cover with 1/2 tomato juice and 1/2 water.
Cover and cook 2 hours or longer, I cook mine for hours.
Better the next day.

title: blueberry dessert pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl combine cake mix, 1 cup oats and 6 teaspoons margarine at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs blend in egg.
Press in prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Meanwhile, to reserved crumbs in same large bowl, add remaining 1/4 cup oats, 2 tablespoons margarine, nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Beat until well mixed.
Remove from oven and spread pie filling.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and return to oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until brown.
Cool completely and cut into wedges or squares.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Place chicken face up in a roasting pan.
Cover with dry onion soup; cover completely with cranberry sauce.
Cover.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake as is, at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover and brown as desired.
Serve hot or cold.
(Can be made as a single or double layer.)

title: imitation artichoke casserole
directions: Brown oil and garlic together.
Add all ingredients; mix should be moist, but not soggy.
If appears too dry, add small olive oil for additional moisture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: fruit smash punch
directions: Mix gelatin with 2 cups of hot water.
Add cold water and fruit juices; stir in sugar.
Just before serving, mash or whip bananas until smooth and creamy.
Beat into mixture.
Add ginger ale the last minute and serve.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise; set aside.
Place half of cornbread in bottom of large bowl.
Top with 1/2 beans.
In medium mixing bowl, combine chopped tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Layer 1/2 this mixture over beans.
Layer 1/2 of cheese, bacon, corn and salad dressing mixture.
Repeat layers. Garnish as desired using cheese, bacon crumbles, black olives, etc.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: melt-in-the-mouth cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt into a bowl and reserve.
Put butter or margarine in large mixer bowl.
Add brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat with mixer or wooden spoon until light and fluffy.
Beat in flour mixture with spoon or mixer, blending until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by scant measuring teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 400° oven for about 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1/2 minute. Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Defrost creamed spinach by boiling 6 minutes.
Season with nutmeg.
Beat egg whites stiff with cream of tartar.
Fold carefully into spinach and bake in a 1-quart souffle dish in a moderate oven (350°) until mixture is well puffed, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: low-fat apple spice cake
directions: In a large bowl mix first eight ingredients.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 24 servings.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Cream water and flour over low heat.
(Beat with whisk as it cooks.)
Let cool. Combine butter, shortening, sugar, vanilla and salt. Mix and whip both together until whipped look appears.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Separate and unroll breadsticks.
Place 3 pepperoni in single layer on 1/2 of breadstick.
Fold the other 1/2 of breadstick over top of pepperoni.
Seal end and twist.
Place on ungreased baking pan.
Combine cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic powder. Sprinkle over top of each breadstick evenly.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with pizza for dipping.
Great for parties or snacks.

title: stir-fried pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from beef, partially freeze and slice thinly across grain into bite size strips.
For sauce, stir together water, soy sauce, bouillon, cornstarch and pepper.
Set aside.
Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Omit cooking oil and salt.
Drain well.
Spray wok or large skillet with nonstick spray. Heat over medium heat; add garlic to pan and stir-fry for 15 seconds.
Add onion; fry for 1 minute.
Add green pepper; fry 2 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Remove vegetables from wok.
Put beef in wok; more oil may be necessary.
Stir-fry 2 or 3 minutes.
Push beef to sides and put sauce in center.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Return vegetables to wok.
Cook 1 minute. Gently stir in tomato wedges.
Heat through.
Serve right away over fettuccine.
Serves 4.

title: easy homemade biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450° and melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix Bisquick, Sprite and sour cream to make dough.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in pan.
Turn over in margarine to coat.
Bake for 15 minutes until brown. (Great with honey and butter.)

title: veal stew-bulgaria(teleshko zadusheno)
directions: Cut veal in 1 inch squares. Cut carrots, onions, and celery into quarters. Cook veal, vegetables, and salt at low heat in 4 cups of water, remove froth while water is boiling. When meat stock is free of froth, cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours at low heat. Add potatoes after veal has cooked for 1 1/2 hours, cook for another 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Serves 4-6.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull berries and reserve half of the best ones.
Mash other half; add cornstarch and sugar.
Cook until thick and clear. Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice; cool and add whole berries.
Pour into pie shell; cover with whipped cream and few whole berries.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crushed graham crackers with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 stick melted butter.
Pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust.

title: rouladen (beef roll-up)
directions: Lay steak on board.
Spread thin layer of mustard and salt and pepper on each steak.
Fill with bacon strips, pickle strips and onion.
Roll up and use toothpicks to hold together.
Brown in a deep skillet on all sides.
Slowly add enough water to fill skillet 1/2 full.
Simmer for 90 minutes.

title: dandelion wine
directions: Combine the blooms with the lemons and add the boiling water; let stand 3 days.
Boil 20 minutes.
When cool, strain through a cloth.
Add the sugar and yeast cake.
Place in jars. Set aside to ferment.
Rack off and seal.
Be careful and be moderate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mom's coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour angel food or bundt pan.
Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix 3 Tbsp. sugar with cinnamon.
Layer 1/2 cake dough and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: apple nut coffeecake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Fold in chopped apples. Spread batter in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and melted butter. Sprinkle over batter and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tomato vegetable soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, bring tomatoes, broth and water to boil. Add vegetables and seasoning.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 1 hour until vegetables are tender.
Yields about 5 1/4 cups.

title: easy vegetable dip for kids
directions: Use with fresh vegetables such as carrots, celery, cucumbers, parsnips, zucchini, peppers, tomatoes, radishes, cabbage, cauliflower, turnips, string beans, onions.

title: hamburger goo
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain the fat.
Add celery, onion, brown sugar, vinegar, dry mustard and ketchup.
Sprinkle flour over mixture.
Stir and mix well.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put diced apples in pan with a little water to keep from sticking.
Mix other ingredients without liquid.
Pour powder mixture over apples.
Top with butter.
Bake at 400° until covered with juices, approximately 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-ham hot dish
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain. Spoon rice into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Place broccoli over rice. Melt butter in a large skillet. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of melted butter over the bread crumbs and set aside. In remaining butter, saute onion until soft. Add flour, salt and pepper, stirring constantly until bubbly. Stir in milk and continue cooking until sauce thickens and bubbles. Cook and stir for 1 minute; add ham and heat through. Pour over rice and broccoli. Sprinkle the crumbs over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with cheese; let stand 5 minutes before serving. Yield: 8 servings.

title: apple spinach salad
directions: Mix together the oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper to make a dressing.

title: scrambled eggs delight
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in milk and seasonings.
Add sausage, bread, cheese and mushrooms, mixing well.
Refrigerate overnight, covered with foil.
In morning heat oven to 350°.
Remove foil.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with toasted cinnamon toast, orange juice or fruit and coffee.

title: brownie chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Line the bottom of the 9 inch spring form pan with wax paper.
Prepare the brownie mix as for chewy brownies.
Bake for 35 minutes or until set.

title: brittle cracker cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place a layer of aluminum foil in an 11 x 16 x 1-inch pan; arrange a single layer of crackers over foil. Combine butter and brown sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes, or until crackers float.
Remove from the oven; sprinkle with chocolate chips over the top.
When chips have melted, spread.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Mix soda and buttermilk.
Add to creamed mixture. Mix oranges, dates, pecans and coconut in large bowl.
Sift flour over this mixture and mix well.
Add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Bake in tube pan (greased and floured) for 2 1/2 hours at 250°.
Keep refrigerated.

title: appetizer ham roll-ups
directions: Spread softened cream cheese over slice of ham.
Roll it up and slice into 4 or 5 sections.
Stick party toothpicks through olive or cheese cube, then through ham roll-up section.
Continue to do this, alternating cheese cubes and olives.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot, except for noodles.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours (on high 4 to 6 hours).
One hour before serving, remove chicken from bone, return meat to crock-pot and add noodles.
Turn on high, cover and cook 1 hour more.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Chop tomatoes, apples and raisins.
Add balance of ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours.
Pack in pint hot pack jars, boiling water bath for 25 minutes.

title: custard pie recipe for 9-inch pan
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and salt together.
Add milk and vanilla. Mix ingredients well and strain into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake in oven preheated to 450° for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes a very delicious pie.

title: curry green tomatoes
directions: Cook green onion in oleo in a large skillet over medium heat until tender.
Stir in curry powder, lemon pepper, garlic powder and Mrs. Dash.
Add tomatoes; cook over low heat until tender.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and raisins; mix well.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: 6 to 8 pork chops

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed and drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Cook in casserole dish until bubbly at 350°.

title: easy cherry dessert
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch cake pan; put pie filling evenly over bottom of pan.
Cover with dry cake mix.
Slice 1/4 pound butter over top of cake mix.
Bake at 375° until bubbly and brown.
May be served with whipped topping.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions.
Remove from oven and punch holes in cake with fork or toothpick.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake and let stand 10 minutes.
Pour caramel ice cream topping over cake and refrigerate.
Put Cool Whip on top of cooled cake and garnish with Heath candy bar pieces.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water.
Chill slightly; blend oranges, cranberry and nuts until slightly thickened.
Turn into 1-quart mold.
Chill until set.
Serve with sour cream or softened cream cheese, blended with small amount of Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: In pan, mix spinach and onion.
Cook according to package directions.
Drain well.
Mix eggs, cheeses, salad dressing, butter and garlic powder.
Add spinach mixture and muffin mix. Cover and chill in refrigerator.
Shape dough into one-inch balls and chill until serving time.
Then place balls on baking sheet and bake at 350° until light brown (about 10 to 12 minutes). Serve warm.
Makes about 60.

title: party cheese bake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put 3/4 of cracker mixture (butter and celery powder).
Spread 2 cups lightly salted onions.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups grated Cheddar cheese.
Combine 3 cups scalded milk, 3 lightly beaten eggs, 1 teaspoon salt and dash of red pepper and pour over crackers.
Sprinkle remainder of cracker mixture.
Top with a light layer of Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Serves about 40.

title: peppery chicken
directions: Combine olive oil, soy sauce, honey, thyme, paprika, cayenne pepper, vinegar, allspice, and pepper. Pour over chicken. Marinate in refrigerator for about 1 hour. Bake chicken at 375° for 30-45 minutes or until cooked through. Surround chicken with sliced mushrooms, spoon the sauce over them and bake 5 minutes more.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and let cool a few minutes.
Roll cheese inside of ham (you will have 6 rolls).
Place rolls in casserole dish. Mix soup, margarine, small amount of lemon juice and 4 dashes of curry powder together and pour this over the rolls of ham and cheese.
Top with can of crushed onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered.

title: crabmeat imperial(serves 4)
directions: Remove cartilage and shell from crabmeat.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute onions and peppers in butter.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in shallow baking dish or in individual ramekins.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Pour dry ingredients into skillet.
Add water and coloring. With skillet on medium-high, stir until mixture pulls from sides of pan.
Take dough from skillet and knead.
Store in airtight container.

title: non-bake cookies
directions: Boil sweet milk, cocoa, white sugar and butter.
Boil for 1 minute and take off stove.
Add peanut butter and oats. Stir real good and drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Combine all ingredients (except graham crust) until texture is smooth. Pour mixture into pie crust and refrigerate for 2 hours. Top with your favorite fruit topping, caramel or even chocolate!

title: date ding bats
directions: Combine and cook slowly 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add vanilla, cereal and nuts.
Form into small balls and roll in coconut or powdered sugar.

title: christmas ornament dough
directions: Mix cornstarch and 1/2 cup cold water in bowl.
Mix salt and 2/3 cup water in an electric skillet or saucepan on low heat. Stir 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately add the cornstarch and cold water mixture to the hot salt water.
This forms an easy-to-handle dough.
This dough will harden to a rock-like consistency.
Great for rolling out and cutting into ornaments for all occasions!

title: fast yeast rolls
directions: Knead and roll out on flour.
Cut out shape with top of glass or etc.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican chicken and tortillas
directions: Saut 1 chopped onion in oil. Add Chili Quick, flour, tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper. Cook slowly about 15 minutes. Add chicken. Fry thin strips of corn tortillas in oil until crisp. On a platter, lay a bed of tortilla chips. Pour chicken sauce over tortillas and top with grated yellow cheese.

title: tofu salad
directions: Crumble tofu.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve on bread or crackers.
See Mustard recipe in Dairy Substitute & Sauces Section.

title: old fashion chocolate pie
directions: Beat together ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix in blender all ingredients, except coconut, for 3 minutes. Bake in a 10-inch pie tin at 350° for 40 minutes.
Put the coconut on top before baking.

title: beef baked in foil
directions: Trim fat from meat; place on large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil. Pour soup over meat. Bring 2 long ends of foil loosely up over meat and double fold. Turn up other sides and double fold. Place in baking dish. Cook for 3 hours in oven at 325° or until tender.

title: chicken thighs with honey basil
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut a piece of aluminum foil 1/2 square foot for each thigh.
Sprinkle the thighs with salt and pepper. In a skillet heat the oil and butter over medium heat.
Brown the thighs for about 2 minutes on each side.
Put a thigh in the middle of each foil square.
Dissolve the honey in the warm chicken stock and drizzle the mixture equally over each thigh. Lay one-eighth of the garlic slices on each thigh.
Cover with a loose layer of the basil leaves and wrap the foil snugly over top.

title: martha louise's chicken casserole
directions: Parboil celery and onion.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: mrs. claus' christmas soup
directions: Wash and soak bean mixture overnight.
Drain off the water. Place beans in a soup pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 4 to 5 hours or all day.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until done; mash.
Add butter and cool enough to handle.
Form balls with a marshmallow in center of each.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yum-chow
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; drain.
Melt oleo.
Add meat, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Cook until brown.
Add tomato soup and water.
Cook slowly for 15 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese triangle and melt slightly.

title: all-purpose barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour over cooked beef or pork ribs and heat in a moderate oven for about 20 minutes.
Or mix with cooked ground beef and onion (fat drained off) for spicy Sloppy Joes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bill lincoln's pot roast
directions: Start at about 9 p.m. Saturday night.
Cut up onion and put in bottom of crock-pot.
Trim roast; cut in half and salt, pepper and flour all sides of roast.
Put roast in pot.
Put one can of golden mushroom soup on top.
Put one can water on top of that. Add one can of tomato sauce.
Set heat on high for about 2 hours, then turn heat to low (don't forget).
When you get up the next morning, turn heat up on high again for about 2 hours.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix eggs with milk; add sugar and pour into crust.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave mexican chili
directions: Place margarine and onions in a large microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir after 2 minutes.
Add ground beef.
Microwave on High 8 minutes or until done.
Stir often. Add chili powder, beans and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Microwave on High 4 minutes or until heated. Stir often.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together. Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs, bananas and sour cream. Beat until blended. Gradually beat in dry ingredients at low speed. Beat until smooth. Fold in berries and pecans. Bake approximately 1 hour. Test for doneness before an hour. Use sharp knife or toothpick.

title: taco dip
directions: Saute garlic and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Use taco chips for dipping.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine apples, raisins and marshmallows.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.
Fold into apple mixture.

title: coconut fruitcake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add fruitcake mix, coconut, raisins and nuts; mix well.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and extract; mix well. Stir in the flour mixture alternately with orange juice.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like pie dough; pat into 2 (9-inch) square pans.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients together in mixer or blender; pour over the warm crust.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Cut while warm into small squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and set aside.

In large bowl (trifle bowl looks great) layer spinach, peas, hard-boiled eggs, bacon, red onion and romaine lettuce and mayonnaise mixture. Then add a thin layer of spinach as last layer and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: biscuits
directions: Measure flour.
Add shortening and cut or rub into the flour. Add the milk a little at a time.
Mix dough.
Roll out about 3 inches thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on baking sheet and bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: deviled crab in shell
directions: In a saucepan, saute the green pepper which has been trimmed and finely chopped.
Also saute the chopped onion in butter for 10 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Remove the pan from the heat and stir in 2 tablespoons brandy, 1 tablespoon each dry and prepared mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the white sauce.
Stir in the crab meat and bread crumbs.
Heat over low heat.
Stir gently.
Spoon into shells.
Sprinkle tops with bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown tops under the broiler for a few minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast on both sides.
Mix Onion soup mix, mushroom soup, mushrooms and burgundy wine.
Pour over browned roast and cook covered at 275 for at least 3 - 4 hours, depending on size of roast.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in greased casserole dish about 3/4 full. Mix together remaining ingredients and spread over cabbage. Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: swiss pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press into bottom and sides of 8-inch pie plate.
Cook bacon; drain and crumble.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Add chopped onion to drippings.
Cook until tender. Add the bacon, onion, Swiss cheese, eggs, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with American cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until an inserted knife comes out clean. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls, roll in sugar and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown.
Take out of oven. Immediately top each cookie with candy kiss.
Press down firmly so cookie crackers around edge.
Cool.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: none left chicken
directions: Boil chicken
until
tender;
cool
and tear into small pieces.
Mix chicken, soup and sour cream together.
Pour into ovenproof dish;
cover
with
crushed
crackers.
Bake in 375° oven until bubbly and light brown on top, about 20 minutes.

title: egg white angel cookies
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Spread waxed paper on 2 cookie sheets. Beat the egg whites very, very stiff, then gradually add 1 cup of sugar.
Add a tiny bit of vanilla.
Add the chopped walnuts and chopped dates.
With teaspoon, place mixture on cookie sheets, about an inch apart.
Bake for 9 minutes, until mixture has a slight film on it.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet with a spatula.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Mix gently and put in greased casserole.
Put in oven at 350° until browned.
May be mixed ahead of time.
If you wish to make larger amount, add 1 can drained green peas.
Serves 6.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in pie filling.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until partially set.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Spread crumbled sausage on bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle the grated cheese over the bread crumbs.
Mix the eggs and milk together and pour over the mixture. Cover the casserole and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
It will keep 48 hours before baking.
Put in cold oven at 350° and bake for 40 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: meringue blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Whip egg whites until frothy.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Beat mixture until it forms stiff peaks.
Drop from a spoon or pipe from a pastry bag with star tip onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Turn heat off in prepared oven and put in cookie sheet.
Do not open oven door for 1 1/2 hours or preferably overnight.
Cool and store in tins.
Serves 20.

title: gingerbread pancakes
directions: Stir all ingredients together mixing well. Place on hot griddle or in frying pan turning once till done.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Put in large bowl and set aside semi-sweet chocolate, German sweet chocolate, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Pour hot solution over chocolate in bowl.
Stir until mixed.
Spread in sheet pan. Let stand several hours.
Makes approximately 4 pounds.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers and thinly slice.
Layer slices in a bowl, salting each layer well.
Set aside for 15 minutes.

title: mushrooms
directions: Soak mushrooms for a few minutes, then drain well and wash. Cut into pieces.
In frying pan, melt butter. Add mushrooms and garlic salt. Cook, covered, about 10 minutes on low heat. Add wine; cook another 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the softened butter and sugar; add eggs.
Alternate, adding dry ingredients and crushed bananas, then add nuts.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured pan until toothpick comes out clean, about 30 minutes to 1 hour, depending on size of pan.

title: most requested punch
directions: Mix and boil the sugar and water.
Add jello and dissolve. Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze; thaw until slushy.
When ready to serve, add 3 (2 liter) bottles ginger ale, 7-Up or Sprite.

title: jenny's ham rolls
directions: Slice dinner rolls lengthwise.
Layer ham and cheese in middle of rolls.
Return tops.
Melt butter.
Add poppy seed, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Pour over tops of rolls and bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Grease or
butter
pan.
Put most of crackers in bottom of pan.
Add peas and asparagus. Spread cream of mushroom soup over vegetables.
Sprinkle
with
almonds.
Add 2 tablespoons asparagus juice.
Dot with butter.
Spread shredded cheese on top. Spread cracker
crumbs
over
that.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 or more.

title: angel eggs
directions: Carefully remove hard-boiled eggs from shell. Cut eggs in half lengthwise. Remove yolk from each egg. Put yolks in small bowl and mash them. Mix in the remaining ingredients. Carefully refill the white halves with the mixture. Arrange on a pretty plate and enjoy!

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour into baking dish.
Now pour fruit over flour mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and milk until it forms a semi-soft ball, stirring constantly.
Add dates and cook until it forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and beat until very thick and creamy.
Pour onto cold, wet cloth.
Roll up and chill.
Slice when cool.

title: cheesy bacon bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese, bacon, onion and pepper in batter bowl.
Separate crescent rolls into 2 rectangles. Pinch seams together.
Spread cheese mixture on each rectangle. Roll up, starting at longest side and seal.
Cut each roll into 16 slices.
Place slices, cut side down, on flat sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm. Yields 32 appetizers.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix together well.
Make tiny balls and place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until browned.

title: microwave corn pudding
directions: In a bowl beat egg, sugar, salt, pepper and cornstarch.
Add corn and milk, blended together.
Put into a buttered baking dish. Cook uncovered in center of oven for 5 minutes.
Stir well from outside in.
Cook 5 minutes more or until set.
Let stand covered 3 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine.
Spread graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Next, spread chocolate chips over crumbs and then
spread oats.
Next, spread nuts over oats and pour milk over all.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lime cooler bars
directions: In a bowl, combine 2 cups flour and the powdered sugar. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Pat into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cream cheese cakes
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft.
Gradually add sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of a cupcake holder and fill to desired amount.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight and top with cherry pie filling.

title: fry bread
directions: Combine eggs and milk in medium bowl.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 3-inch squares. Gently place squares a few at a time in deep hot oil (375°).
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels. Serve warm with butter and honey.
Yields 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: layered enchiladas
directions: Use 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom of dish with 1/2 cup enchilada sauce.
Put 4 of the torn corn tortillas next. Arrange shredded chicken to cover.
Add chicken broth, 1/2 cup cheese, green chiles and 1/4 cup olives.
Top with rest of tortillas, sauce, cheese and black olives.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix together apple pie filling, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon. Place in greased cake pan.
Pour cake mix over top.
Slice margarine and place on top of this.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice sugar cookie dough in 1/4-inch slices; place on a pizza pan.
Edges will run together when baked at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar and cream cheese; spread on cooled cookie layer.
Spread strawberry pie filling over cream cheese mixture.
Arrange bananas and pineapple chunks around on top of strawberry filling.
Top all with the Cool Whip. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Rinse cranberries well; remove any stems.
Place all ingredients in a food processor or blender.
Chop until finely grated.
Add more sugar if desired.
Chill at least three hours so flavors blend.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate-citrus cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; blend until smooth. Pour over crushed ice.
Top with a small scoop of ice cream.

title: peach crunch
directions: Place peaches in the bottom of a 13 x 9 pan. Sprinkle with sugar, then sprinkle with jello. Drizzle water over, then sprinkle dry cake mix over the whole thing. Drizzle with butter. Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes. Note that this can be used with other fruit and jello.

title: sweet-and-sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, oats, milk, onion, pepper and salt.
Mix well. Shape into about 30 small balls.
Brown in hot shortening; drain. Combine catsup, Worcestershire, vinegar, sugar and water; mix well.
Pour sauce over meatballs.
Simmer 30 minutes over low. Heat until ready to serve.

title: chili salad
directions: In salad bowl, combine lettuce, corn chips, tomato, pepperoni, olives and cheese.

title: seven layer untossed salad
directions: Layer the vegetables as listed.
Spread mayonnaise on top of the vegetables.
Sprinkle sugar on mayonnaise.
Next, put on crumbled bacon, then add the eggs.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: hazel's sticky buns
directions: The night before serving:
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan well. Spread nuts over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle raisins on top. Sprinkle brown sugar over all.
Arrange rolls on top with enough room to rise.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.
Melt butter and add second 1/2 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls. Leave uncovered overnight on counter.
Bake next morning at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sherry's bacon spaghetti
directions: Brown bacon and set aside.
Use about 1/3 cup of bacon drippings to saute onions.
Add tomato sauce.
When spaghetti is done, drain and add sauce.
Toss with bacon.
A whole different taste to spaghetti.

title: caribbean banana chicken
directions: Flatten chicken, arrange ham slice on top.
Peel banana and cut into thirds crosswise and cut each third in half.
Place 1 banana piece on top of ham slice.
Roll chicken-ham-banana like an eggroll, enclosing banana and ham inside.

title: peach delight cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 2 round pans, 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inches. Drain peaches, reserving syrup. Add enough water to reserved syrup to measure 1 1/4 cups. Prepare cake mix as directed on package, except substitute syrup mixture for the water. Pour batter into pans. Bake and cool as directed. Cut peaches into bite size pieces. Mix yogurt and whipped topping; fold in peaches. Fill layers with about half of the peach mixture. Spoon remaining peach mixture over top of cake. Refrigerate 2 hours or until chilled.

title: easy one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, the ham and onion powder in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick mix and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs and milk.
Stir, while cooking over medium heat, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix well.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Blend together last 4 ingredients in separate bowl.
When blended together, pour over top of raw cake mixture.
Bake as it says on box for time and temperature.
Grease bottom of cake pan, not sides.
Rectangular cake pan works best.
When cool, sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: quick, easy, good baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Bake until bubbly and dried down good.
Also good with wieners or franks buried in mixture.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Mix the eggs, margarine, sweetener and raisins together, then add the dry ingredients, which have been mixed together.
Mix this together, then add the applesauce and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar, oil and vanilla, mixing until thick.
Add zucchini and stir.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients.
Add to other mixture, stirring well.
Add nuts and lemon rind.
Bake in greased cake pans or Bundt cake pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Dot top with butter.
Cover.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish lightly with Pam.
Place breasts in single layer in pan.
Sprinkle soup mix over chicken.
Pour nectar over all.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious.

title: crab and shrimp
directions: Mix all together.
Place in greased casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Serves 6.

title: christine's hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, then peel and slice.
Cook bacon until crispy; drain fat.
Slice onions in same pan as you fried bacon and add water, vinegar and sugar.
Cover and simmer until onions are soft. Crunch up bacon into pan with onions.
Thicken with flour or cornstarch and then add potatoes.
Make all gone.
Eat and enjoy.

title: the best fudge ever
directions: Mix butter, Velveeta, powdered sugar and cocoa together.
Add vanilla; mix together.
Spread the fudge into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Let harden and then cut into squares.

title: delicious fried onions
directions: Slice onions into thick slices; soak for 30 minutes in bowl of milk.
Dip onions into egg, then flour.
Drop onion slices into hot grease and brown.
Salt before serving.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat in 9 x 13 pan and bake at 300° until slightly brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, 4 1/2 ounces Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread on crust.
Spread 1/3 of 13 1/2-ounce Cool Whip on top.
Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Spread on top of mixture, then spread remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: crystal salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan and heat to boiling.
Cook for 1 minute on medium heat.
Cool.
Stir in other ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch flat cake pan.
Bake cake mix according to package directions.
While still warm, puncture top with holes at 2-inch intervals.
Carefully pour Kahlua over top of hot cake.
Let cool; cut into cubes.
Make up the chocolate mousse.
Place 1/2 the cake cubes in bottom of pretty serving bowl.
Top with 1/2 the chocolate mousse mixture.
Top with 1 carton Cool Whip.
Top with 4 crushed Heath bars.
Repeat layers, except reserve the last 4 crushed Heath bars to place on top of dessert when it is served. Cover with Saran Wrap.
Allow to chill for at least six hours.
Can be made a day ahead.
To serve, top with remaining Heath bar pieces and spoon out servings.

title: cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Set aside. Combine cake mix, cherry pie filling, eggs, and flavoring.
Stir, using a wooden spoon, until all ingredients are well mixed.
Pour batter into prepared pan, and bake at 350° until a wooden toothpick inserted in center come out clean.
Set aside to cool.

title: wheat germ and oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine oil, honey and molasses.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Combine soy flour and milk powder.
Add raisins, nuts, salt, wheat germ and oatmeal.
Stir wet ingredients into dry ingredients and blend well.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 10 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat 5 minutes, until sugar is dissolved.
Add eggs, one at a time, plain flour and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Can be baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan. Let cool and then sprinkle with powdered sugar or add strawberries and Cool Whip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie crust.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 375° until set and pastry is nicely browned.
Approximate cooking time: 50 minutes.

title: ginger dressing for fruit
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small saucepan; gradually add juice, stirring until smooth.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat and boil one minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour over assorted fruits; toss gently, chill.

title: b-l-t soup
directions: In an 8-quart pot, lightly saute diced bacon.
Do not remove drippings.
Add margarine.
Heat until melted.
Add chopped lettuce.
Saute 3 minutes.
Add flour.
Stir until well blended. Cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken stock, tomatoes, nutmeg and pepper. Heat until boiling, stirring to prevent sticking.
When mixture begins to boil, add half and half.
Warm, but do not boil.
Serves 12.

title: rancher's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into shell and bake until firm and slightly brown.	The center won't be as firm as the other edges, but will set when cooled. (Do not overbake.)

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground round and onion in a Dutch oven or similar pan. Add the remaining ingredients, EXCEPT rice. Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat. Add rice. Simmer for about 5 minutes. Makes approximately 12 cups.

title: viennese toffee torte
directions: Mix cool whip and crushed candy bar.
Split cake in half lengthwise.
Fill and frost cake.
Chill and serve.

title: one egg cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, beating thoroughly.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 2 or 3 layer pans at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes, depending on number of layers.
Cool. Ice with Chocolate Caramel, Lemon Buttercream of Strawberry Seven Minute Icing.

title: mrs. jimmie carter's cheese ring
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Press into ring mold and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, unmold on plate.
Fill center with preserves.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: grandma's chocolate bonbons
directions: Melt butter slowly and add milk.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Add coconut and pecans.
Chill until it can be easily handled.
Roll in balls.
Place in freezer until firm.
Melt cocoa and Gulf wax together in the top of double boiler.
Remove from heat and dip each candy into chocolate mixture with toothpick quickly and place on wax paper.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Fix in coffeepot.
Put cider, lemonade and orange juice in bottom of pot.
Put sugar, cinnamon sticks and spices in basket of coffeepot.
Perk until done!

title: watergate cake with impeachment frosting
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl, then beat at medium mixer speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool on rack.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Put in layers as given and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Use a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan or dish.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well, being careful to prevent the cubed chicken from becoming shredded.
Serve open face on a leaf of lettuce over a sliced croissant roll, garnished with tomato slice, dill pickle wedge and potato chips.
This recipe keeps well overnight in refrigerator without losing its fresh flavor.
Happy Eating!

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Melt margarine.
Beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Do not add water, boil syrup until it hardens (not brittle). Add water the last thing, add soda to improve color.
Pour over corn, mix well and make into balls.
Do not pop corn with oil, just plain popcorn.
Butter your hands very good to keep from sticking.
